Orchestrated workflow using Finite State Machine and other Scala language features such as implicits and pattern matching.\n\nDesigned JMX Scala Client to connect to JMX to gather memory usage and Garbage Collection information, use Lens library to modify the some statistics case classes elegantly and try to use the statistics to analyse the relationship between Garbage Collection and service timeout.\n\nAlso wrote many integration tests using this framework to test the backend system and reproduced some hard to reproduce problems when using manual testing approach. \n\nWorked on Apache Hadoop ZooKeeper, Thrift and Scala Shapeless Library.', u'title': u'Test Automation for Server Component'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.9 ~ 2014.1', u'description': u'Developed an easy to use automation framework for functional test of a complex portal application with AJAX functions and training offshore team members to get up to speed with Selenium Automation, jBehave BDD and the framework I developed. \n\nThe automation framework now is open sourced on github in Java 8, https://github.com/yujunliang/seleniumcapsules\n\nAlso enabled unit testing for entire application using PowerMock and provided reference implementation for all modules.', u'title': u'Test Automation Framework'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2009.6 ~ 2009.12', u'description': u'Agero provides a complete, turnkey solution for connecting the vehicle to the digital highway, offering our automotive and insurance clients the ability to provide consumers with connectivity and advanced technology services at the drivers\u2019 fingertips. As a result, our automotive and insurance clients access the latest in technology expertise, with greater options for merging their customers\u2019 lifestyle with drivestyle. Drivers can confidently focus on the road ahead while Agero clients leave the competition behind.', u'title': u'Infiniti Connection[TM]'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.2 ~ 2013.3', u'description': u'Developed CCP Collateral, CCP Swaps applications which interoperating with clearing houses and brokerage firms on Grails/Groovy platform. Introduced framework and reference implementation for functional test automation using Spock and Selenium 2. Designed easy to use API to read, write from HTML form, Menu Navigation and encapsulation of waiting mechanism inside click event. Combined other open source technologies for end to end testing of web workflow for Accounting, Pricing and Custody operations from Data Entry, File Upload to CSV/Excel/PDF Report generation. Coached the team to get up to speed with the framework and implement functional tests for mission critical process to ensure bug free releases. Actively evolved this Grails Plugin to maintain the usability for variant application flavors.\n\nAdvocated Behavior Driven Development methodology as the initial phase towards Continuous Delivery and DevOps. Used this approach to assist the system upgrade to support Windows 7 and latest Jasper Report libraries and achieved 0 bugs on UAT for Collateral Management, Retail Future Merge and MBK Stratification.\n\nReviewed applications to distill effective design solutions as architecture artifacts to serve the future development using Emergent Design methodology and made the code base much cleaner and leaner.', u'title': u'Fidelity RAD - Rapid Agile Development'}]

summary: I re:Invented myself from a Java Developer to a Cloud Architect!\n\nI am a Senior Solution Architect for Deloitte Consulting LLP. We help our clients to onboard Cloud. I am passionate about Cloud Computing and I got all 5 certifications from AWS last year. How did I pass 5 AWS certifications including 2 on professional level in 4 months? I spent all my nights and weekends studying it. \n\nI worked for ThoughtWorks, the company who defined DevOps, Agile, Continuous Integration, Continuous Delivery, Behavior Driven Development and Selenium WebDriver. I am a long time Ruby developer which is used by Chef DevOps tool. \n\nI also had experience working as a Agile Coach to help the teams transforming to Agile Development environment, offering guidance and direction on Agile Software Development such as TDD, BDD and DevOps.\n\nI have deep domain knowledge in financial industry since I worked for many major banks in the world including Deutsche Bank, UBS, Credit Suisse, JPMorganChase, Macquarie Bank and Westpac. I used to be an expert in Domain Driven Design using Design Patterns and Enterprise Architecture Patterns to solve complex problems and since the inception of cloud, I successfully transit myself into an Enterprise Architect with focus on Cloud Infrastructure on Big Data Machine Learning and SAP. \n  \nAnd I am continuous learning and continuous improving, relentlessly. Life is short, do what matters!\n\n

For partial list look here. Peter is a certified a Master Black Belt and holds an MS degree in Statistics from Iowa State and a BS in Chemical Engineering from Purdue. Peter worked for 3M over 10 years where he gained extensive experience applying Sigma Methodologies to a variety of processes.\n\nPeter has successfully developed Six Sigma deployment strategies and training for Product and Process Development, Manufacturing and Business Process Improvement. His broad experience across many technologies helped him gain insight on how to apply Six Sigma methods to Business Processes. (see below)\n\nPeter has traveled internationally over 100 times to lead international projects, led Six Sigma Deployment, lead workshops for managers, business analysts, engineers, process and product developers. Peter has developed and presented numerous waves in Six Sigma and workshops in Design of Experiments, Mixture Experimentation, Statistical Process Control, Test Method improvement and development, Statistical Thinking and Business Process Charting to thousands.\n\nSpecialties: Lean Six Sigma Master Black Belt for all Industries.

summary: Seymore D’ Fair (a.k.a. Seymour D. Fair) is a funny cartoon & costume character who was the official mascot of the 1984 Louisiana World Exposition.  His witty name is derived from the N’Awlins “Yat” phrase “See more of the fair”.  A cartoon character creation by artist Robert Whitney and Gary Goddard, celebrated theme park and Walt Disney costume designer, Seymore is not your ordinary cartoon and mascot character. He has the unique distinction of being the “World’s 1st-Ever” character mascot in the history of Bureau International des Expositions World’s Fairs &  Expositions (circa 1851).\n\nFrom Los Angeles to New York to Paris, Seymore performed on the world stage promoting the World’s Fair.  In the Big Easy he and his best friend Pepe’ la Gator entertained 7,000,000+ visitors bringing smiles and laughter to all who experienced their magnanimous personalities.  \n\nSeymore had many notable moments during his reign.  Once while in France, he was escorted out of the Louvre for being too ‘spectacular’.  During the 1984 Republican National Convention, he made a big splash rubbing feathers on stage with the likes of George H. W. Bush, Vice-President of the United States.  Back in Washington DC, he hung out with Billy Joel at the White House entertaining wives of Russian Diplomats.  Seymore even appeared on Saturday Night Live, shown guarding an entrance to the White House with Secret Service Agents!\n \t\nSeymore’s whimsical & magical personality contributed greatly to him becoming the most recognizable World's Fair mascot in the modern age of International Expositions and World’s Fairs.  His exemplary contributions to Louisiana, World Expositions, and the Bureau International Expositions organization earned him an exhibition & induction into the Louisiana State Museum and the Smithsonian - National Museum of American History.\n\nEMAIL:  email.me@seymoredfair.com \nWIKIPEDIA: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seymore_D._Fair\nTHE SEYMORE D' FAIR FOUNDATION: www.seymoresfoundation.org

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'', u'description': u'HyperWM is an annual unconference, bringing together local government officers and members, hyperlocal bloggers, and other interested parties, in the English West Midlands.\n\nBrewCamp is a spin off event, held bi-monthly, discussing related issues in a relaxed, informal setting.', u'title': u'HyperWM & BrewCamp'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.4 ~ now', u'description': u'Free Access to multi-lingual, mobile-friendly content for visitors to museums, historic properties and other sites.', u'title': u'QRpedia'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.9 ~ 2013.9', u'description': u'State of the Map is OpenStreetMap's annual conference. The 2013 edition was held in Birmingham, UK. It was a three day event for everyone contributes to and/or uses OpenStreetMap. 300 people from all over the world participated in the conference. From volunteer mappers to professionals who make a living on providing services on top of OpenStreetMap.\n\nAs well as assisting with the initial bid to host the conference, and the setup, I chaired the main strand for all three days.\n\nThe attendees gave the conference an average score of 8.1 (out of 10).', u'title': u'State of the Map conference 2013'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.9 ~ now', u'description': u'HealthCampWM is an unconference for people working (or interested in) using social media in Health and Wellbeing in the West Midlands to get together for a day and talk about their work.\n\n\u2018What\u2019s an \u2018unconference\u2019?\u2019 I hear you cry \u2013 well, it\u2019s a participant driven event that laughs in the face of those traditional top-down, boring, un-interactive conferences \u2013 death by Powerpoint it ain\u2019t! Mingling with experts in social media, online communities, digital engagement and open data, this event allows you to choose the topics you want to discuss, share, and learn about.\n\nThere is no charge to attend, and there is no agenda to adhere to - you will help to shape the event and get from it, and contribute to it, what you want/need.', u'title': u'Health Camp West Midlands 2012'}]

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2014.5 ~ 2014.5', u'description': u'For the remembrance of Shirley Eder ( June 2, 1923 - 2013) and her Prince Joseph H. Laird (1921 - April 1, 2012)\n\nThere, Shirley had three children. The church and vicarage being located in a rural area called \u201cChurch Hill,\u201d Shirley fulfilled a lifelong dream by buying a horse. She soon added three more and opened a riding school called \u201cChurch Hill Ups.\u201d Six years later, the Lairds moved to Wayne, where they lived in a house on the Rosengarten estate, \u201cChanticleer,\u201d now a botanical garden. During this time, she returned to journalism, serving on the editorial staff of the Montgomery County Newspapers, and writing a weekly column called \u201cOnce over Lightly.\u201d In the \u201960s and \u201970s, she became publications manager for Vincent G. Kling and Associates, Architects. She continued writing her column until leaving to become an entrepreneur. Her business, \u201cLaird Unlimited Editorial Services,\u201d provided wordsmith and public relations services to two dozen clients. In addition to her employment, she served for 20 years on the board of COLLAB, Philadelphia Museum of Art; she was on the vestry of St. David\u2019s Episcopal Church, Radnor; and she was publicity chairperson for the Chestnut Hill Committee of the Philadelphia Orchestra.', u'title': u'Laird Unlimited Editorial Services'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2017.3 ~ now', u'description': u'This project spawned from a couple past disputes on en.wikipedia.org... Editorial/Authoritarian control vs. User space 'freedom of speech' is really about inclusion of knowledge-base pertinent not-to-all but serve a self-interest foremost. This is VERY contemporary issue. I am interested in making some progress without being burned by flame wares. What I discovered is that User: [space] is no different than 'official' articles. How come those editors didn't see that? We need to 'ban' human editors from 'deleting' human users manual input data, instead, offering to move user's input from 'official' root to User: space... or put in a 'time-delay' of speedy deletion by a script according to system resource constraints. This is on the one hand about respect for human labor, and on the other, a respect for those who understands Machine Intelligence better than their own intelligence. As far as current practices of those army of novice wiki editors, if they shouldn't be called neo nazi soldiers, I would say there is BIG impedance mis-match between their exercise of easy-earned editorial power vs. extensive reading on a certain subject, dear and near to the hearts of data and other substance entry from all walks of common folks.\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_talk:Allthingsgo\nI am also interested in looking into perceived system bias of wikipedia.org and what ought to be the foundation of finding A middle way for each visitor or tomb robber in due time ?\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Systemic_bias', u'title': u'reformation on wikipedia.org wiki articles'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.5 ~ 2015.5', u'description': u'volunteer/documenting and tester for Garry Morrison's FeynmanKnowledgeEngine hosted on github.com ', u'title': u'Semantic Web + Python'}]

summary: I am a builder of communities, with over five years of experience in community development, management and engagement.  My passion is in finding intersections between content production, community growth and user empowerment, building on my research interests in the social relations and power structures of online communities, technology and its relationship with the developing world, and the future of the Internet as a medium of expression for the un(der)represented, interconnecting them with political theory and the study of international relations.\n\nI am a graduate of the Ateneo de Manila University in the Philippines, one of Southeast Asia's leading universities, where I earned my bachelor's degree in Political Science, majoring in Global Politics alongside a minor in Chinese Studies. In addition to my four years at the Ateneo de Manila, I also spent three terms (roughly one year) studying abroad: one term in China and two in Poland.  My specializations include languages (I speak seven to varying levels of fluency, including English), non-profit management, research and analysis, foreign policy and international affairs, and writing.\n\nI look forward to shaping the future of interpersonal interaction between people for both online properties and other organizations, building a career in technology, research and analysis, consulting (especially on foreign policy), government, the non-profit sector, and the media.  I also look forward to challenging myself and expanding my skill set through entering other fields.  In addition, I am a citizen of both the Philippines and the United States, and I am legally able to work in either country (or both).

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2009.2 ~ 2009.2', u'description': u'A collaborative project initiated by Scott Kildall and Nathaniel Stern, Wikipedia Art was originally intended to be art composed on Wikipedia, and thus art that anyone can edit. Since the work itself manifested as a conventional Wikipedia page, would-be art editors were required to follow Wikipedia\u2019s enforced standards of quality and verifiability; any changes to the art had to be published on, and cited from, \u2018credible\u2019 external sources: interviews, blogs, or articles in \u2018trustworthy\u2019 media institutions, which would birth and then slowly transform what the work is and does and means simply through their writing and talking about it. Wikipedia Art, we asserted at its creation, may start as an intervention, turn into an object, die and be resurrected, etc, through a creative pattern / feedback loop of publish-cite-transform that we called \u201cperformative citations.\u201d Despite its live mutations through continuous streams of press online, Wikipedia Art was considered controversial by those in the Wikipedia community, and removed from the site 15 hours after its birth. But the debate and discussion there, and later in the art blogosphere and mainstream press, produced a notable work after all. These communities still \u201ctransform what the work is and does and means simply through their writing and talking about it,\u201d despite its absence from Wikipedia.', u'title': u'Wikipedia Art'}]

summary: Pete Forsyth is an Internet and communications consultant with deep expertise in online peer production communities, specifically the production of open educational resources using wiki-based web sites like Wikipedia.\n\nAs the Wikimedia Foundation's first Public Outreach Officer, Forsyth worked with the vast international network of volunteer Wikipedia contributors. He was a key architect of the Wikipedia Public Policy Initiative, an innovative pilot project to support professors in using Wikipedia writing as a teaching tool.\n\t\t\nForsyth first began writing Wikipedia articles as a volunteer in 2006, focusing on the history of his home state of Oregon. He helped found WikiProject Oregon, a dynamic group of Wikipedians which coordinates collaborative projects and coordinates with local institutions. Prior to joining the Wikimedia Foundation staff in 2009, Pete provided communication services to non-profit, business, and political clients, and worked for several news organizations.\n\n• Founder and leader of volunteer communities, online and offline\n• Highly skilled writer and verbal communicator\n• Accomplished negotiator, collaborative strategic thinker, facilitator of diverse stakeholder groups\n• Extensive experience with Internet technology, local government and politics\n• Passionate about engaging humanity in broad collaboration through use of online tools and free licenses\n\nSpecialties: Wikipedia, Open Educational Resources, Online peer production, writing and editing (grants, business plans, reports, press releases). Strong background in Internet tools and resources (Wikipedia, Wordpress, Twitter, Facebook, YouTube, Google, etc.) Strong international professional network.

summary: In last seven years, Subhashish has built, managed, and catalyzed the growth of hundreds of communities and outreach programs at Mozilla, Centre for Internet and Society (CIS), and Wikimedia Foundation. \n\nLed Mozilla's Community Development across Asia; Helped sharpen its focus on Diversity and Inclusion; Built momentum for the Indian community restructuring; Shaped Mozilla’s global communications strategy for the Campus Clubs program; Launched a user research to assess the state of Open Source across 20 top tech, design and law universities in India.\n\nAt Wikimedia Foundation and CIS together, built and implemented the Wikimedia strategic plans for India; increased Wikipedia’s reach (readers) by more than 60% (3x global readership) in and participation (editors) by 50% [as compared to ~10% global growth] in 6 Indian languages; Designed and launched Wikipedia Education program in 5 Indian languages to 2400 students; Led Wikipedia Outreach Program to educate over 4000 potential Wikipedia editors in more than 200 focused outreach programs; Produced extensive Open Educational Resources (OER) in 7 Indian languages; Instrumental in bringing over 200 encyclopedic and literary works under Creative Commons licenses by collaboration with more than 50 authors, publishers, and Galleries, Libraries, Archives and Museums (GLAM); and led liaison with Indian state governments to launch Kiwix, the offline Wikipedia.\n\nWinner of the 2015 Opensource.com People’s Choice Award for covering open source-related highlights, and awarded as \

summary: I am an Assistant Professor at the Department of Computer and Information Sciences at the University of Alabama at Birmingham. My area of interest is cloud computing, systems security, and database systems.\n\n\nPreviously, I was an NSF Computing Innovation Fellow and Assistant Research Scientist at the Department of Computer Science, Johns Hopkins University. \n\nBefore that, I was a PhD candidate at the Department of Computer Science, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. I received my PhD in Computer Science in October 2009, and was supervised by Prof. Marianne Winslett (UIUC) and Prof. Radu Sion (Stony Brook).\n\nSpecialties: Cloud Computing, Secure Provenance, Authentication, Access Control. projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2013.1 ~ now', u'description': u'In 2006, we've set-up ProWAM.tk - a cooperative with some 15.000 agro-families in the Unesco World Heritage Region of Togo-Burkina Faso-Ghana and B\xe9nin.  Together we've planted some 1,5 million trees, restoring river beds, field delimitations against elephants etc, erosion and at the same time as a group-restoration initiative.  Now there are tons of fruits and herbs coming out of the forests.  The oily fruits, we press them and transform them into soap.  Local soap manufacturing knowledge resulted in a return of 42%.  Our/my R&D Dpt. managed to push that 42% return to over 600% ! So before, soap made with a 100 \u20ac investment=cost returned 142 \u20ac=42% return.  Our R&D dpt developed e.g. a Jatropha soap with medicinal vertues against skin deseases/rash/pimples.  This soap gives a return of over 600%.  Interested in co-investing? We write out investment bonds with a very interesting return interest.  Just contact us to discuss to what extent investing in us can be interesting and profitable to you.', u'title': u'R&D Dpt in the Soap Manufacturing plant of ProWAM.tk - Cooperative'}, {u'timePeriod': u'1990.1 ~ now', u'description': u'It is 3 things:\n1. a sustainable building where workshops are given, there is a labo and a workshop to repair tractors/trucks/vehicles and to make things.  Around the building are fields where permaculture is demonstrated and micro-businesses, s.a. soap manufacturing plant, chicken and fish farm, etc. There is a shop where the products are sold and trainees learn marketing and managing a shop as they learned during the advanced courses on Business Management taught in the Leadership Development Institute for graduates on the topic in the regular education system.\n2. the sustainable building is accompanied by a virtual side of itself.  Trainees and coaches continue their real world workshops and lessons there.  It also constitutes a network environment where former and nowaday students can meet to reinforce and accellerate their missions.\n3. the Leadership Development Institute also has an own investment fund that allows third parties to invest and get a return on their investment and helps fund the students business proposals/micro-businesses.', u'title': u'Leadership Development Institute for the first ladies of a country'}]

summary: Institution:BHILAI  STEEL PLANT \nJoining & Retirement: 10 Mar 1977 to 31 Aug 2014\n\nI am an electrical engineer, Computer Software and Hardware professional. My Electrical Engg education was completed in 1976. In 1982 I took Computer hard ware training in Kiev, then USSR. In 1984 I passed Industrial Engineering, a master degree equivalent.  In 1985 my Electronics paper came in magazine ‘Industrial Electronics Equipment Design’ A McGraw-Hill New York publication. In 1990 I presented a paper ( RO-56) “Adaptive trajectory databases for Manipulator control” in International Conference on Automation, Robotics and Computer Vision (ICARCV ’90),  Sept, 1990, in Singapore. 1992 onwards I started in fundamental physics. I thought it is very interesting to try to solve the singularity free N-Body problem from Newton times. I started presenting papers in many parts of world that time on word till today in Physics. Retired from BSP at the age 60 after 37.5 years of service.\n\nI worked in various departments in Steel Plant, Electrical and  Process control computer section. \n\nLast 8 years I worked in C&IT- SAP PM Module.  Mapping of new departments,  Master data up-dating, (Codes and Catalogs, Equipment up-loading etc.)  Guiding and teaching customers, Creation and retrieval of maint notifications, Orders etc. Good experience in  SAP BI, HANA. \n\nIn Dec 2014, I passed with high grades in exams conducted by SAP in the course 'Extending SAP Products with SAP HANA Cloud Platform \nhttps://open.sap.com/verify/xekev-gorip-domok-hocuc-nokyz\n\nand  'Next Steps in Software Development on SAP HANA'  \nhttps://open.sap.com/verify/xoraf-famef-nomok-tares-tufoc\n \nIn addition Books by me:\nhttp://vaksdynamicuniversemodel.blogspot.in/p/books-published.html\n\nPresentations in Physics & HANA  please see my CV\n\nhttp://vaksdynamicuniversemodel.blogspot.in/p/cv.html\n\nhttps://skydrive.live.com/?lc=16393#!/?cid=485CC4B593A12043&id=485CC4B593A12043!135!cid=485CC4B593A12043&id=485CC4B593A12043!135

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2012 ~ 2012', u'description': u'Exploring systematic reviews as a means of identifying the shortcomings of currently available nonanimal research models to provide the kinds of information for which researchers currently rely on animal models.', u'title': u'Strategic Roadmap from Animal-Based Research Models to Nonanimal Research Alternatives'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.11 ~ 2012.4', u'description': u'Sprawling and adventurous, bringing together key legal insights important in the business case for making multi-unit dwellings smoke-free in America - and elsewhere.  There's little evidence that urban migration in North America, Europe, or elsewhere on Earth will slow or reverse.  Multi-unit dwelling will become a major fact of human life; resolving its inherent problems is more and more urgent, and smoking (anything) is a life-critical threat to human health of everyone in the buildings.', u'title': u'Implementation of Zero Tolerance Smoke-Free Building Policy in Multi-Unit Residential High-Rise'}, {u'timePeriod': u'1994.6 ~ 1995.9', u'description': u'The 8th (Aug 6-13, 1995) in San Diego, California, was the 1st time EU-based Vegans International (VI) held an International Vegan Festival in the Western Hemisphere.  My role as program planner involved working with VI and US-based American Vegan Society as VP of VUNA (Vegetarian Union of North America, the International Vegetarian Union's North American arm) to produce an attractive, worthwhile, and profitable educational and recreational program to fund 3 organizations.  \n\nWe sited the 8-day event, established event logistics with long-time conference partner, American Vegan Society (Jay and Freya Dinshah), and invited and scheduled speakers (I negotiated compensation and amenities with each of them) and vegan-related vendors and exhibitors.\n\nThis General Event Overview gives a flavor of the event:\n*  A world of friendship with vegans and vegetarians of North America (United States, Canada, Mexico); South and Central America; Europe, Middle East, Asia, Africa, Australia\n*  A world of learning from the knowledge of educators, professionals, movement leaders from around the planet.\n*  A world of kindness in planning and helping to make a better kind of world.\n*  A world of recreation with music, dance, and entertainment on a beautiful campus in a great vacation area.\n*  Side trips to Mexico.\n*  Festival meals were 100% VEGAN prepared under the direction of Certified Executive Chef Ron Pickarski, CEC, Winner of several Silver and Bronze (later Gold) medals in the International Culinary Olympics Author \', u'title': u'8th International Vegan Festival, San Diego, California'}, {u'timePeriod': u'1999 ~ 1999', u'description': u'Under-employed dietitians, nutrition educators, nutritionists, culinary gurus, and others who are vegans who have dared to commit their scientific and educational careers to empowering the food side of veganism often are short of cash.\n\nSuch vegan food professional who understands food offer to nonvegetarian restaurants VEGAN-ized menus for modest fee, then  studies pre-existing menu, comprehends what could QUICKLY be 'veganized' by substituting inexpensive, commonly-found vegan items for animal products, then types out each recipe. \nRepeat process for each menu items which can be 'veganized' and word process in simple format the LISTED collection of all 'veganized' menu options.  Legal, IP, and business terms and conditions apply.\n\nThe vegan food professional also offers to coach the kitchen staff ('back of the house') on vegan food substitutions and to coach the serving personnel and host(s)/ess(es) and managers on how to attract, support, please, and retain veg(etari)an diners.\nThe restaurant management is taught how more vegan items can be more profitable (less spoilage, thus less shrinkage or food loss).\n\nPossible synergy could be a two-fold advertising program.\n\nMaintain websites for local vegetarian group(s), featuring \u2018veganized\u2019 menu clients on local vegetarian society\u2019s website.  Link opens ONLY to a CUSTOMIZED all-vegan-appropriate PAGE with (a) the restaurant\u2019s all-vegan menu AND the restaurant\u2019s appropriate contact information and hours, and a pop-up MAP (perhaps with travel directions from a typed in location).  Also, the restaurant could offer a 10% discount on vegetarian (vegan) items ONLY to veg society members (when their show their vegetarian society or vegan association cards).\n\xa9 Maynard S. Clark - http:// Maynard.Clark.GooglePages.com\n\xa9 Maynard.Clark@.GMail.com\n', u'title': u'Veganizing Mainstream Restaurant Menus'}, {u'timePeriod': u'', u'description': u'* Mandarin speakers want to practice English (and reduce their Chinese accents)? \n* English speakers want to learn Mandarin? \n* Nerdy Chinese folks want to bring friends and have a fun, FREE \', u'title': u'Weekly Tuiesday Evening Mandarin-English Chat at Harvard Chan School of Public Health'}]

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2010.9 ~ 2011.5', u'description': u'A novel method of clustering which defines a density level for each data point with respect to the effect of other points on them. According to the exerted densities, it generates a directed graph from the dataset. The algorithm can predict the number and also the shapes of clusters and visualize them so as to be interpreted by experts.', u'title': u'A New Approach for Density-Based Clustering (Dissertation)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2007.7 ~ 2010.2', u'description': u'A new 2-dimentional Skeletonization algorithm was designed, implemented and compared with a number of recent applicable methods. Examining the effect of further points on each point, instead of only its 8 neighbors, with novel results regarding running time and accuracy.', u'title': u'A New Approach for the Skeletonization of Arabic/Farsi Handwriting in Gray Scale Images (Dissertation)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.1 ~ 2014.1', u'description': u'This is a project for pervasive interaction design class. During this project, we will work as a team to design a solution for people with disability to better access various facilities. The design is futuristic and involves many ideas that may not be implementable for the time being. The whole idea of this project is for us to gain better understanding of techniques in pervasive interaction design. \n\nMethods used include::\nSketch, create scenarios,\nInterview, diary study, user enactment\nLow-fi prototype\n', u'title': u'Pervasive Interaction Design for People with disability'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.1 ~ 2014.4', u'description': u'\u201cNavable\u201d, a wearable interactive map optimized for people with mobility disability. It is a solution designed specifically for solving mobility problems that our target users may encounter. Navable can work in both indoor and outdoor environments, navigate users to destinations, be capable of remembering users' pattern of regular routes, alert users to potential dangers, allow users to report and receive real-time contextual data, and enable users to remotely control environments. The desired experience that Navable intends to deliver is to foresee accessibility issues that user will encounter, solve accessibility problems that users are having, and remember/report past issues to prevent them from happening again.', u'title': u'Navable'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2010.5 ~ 2010.5', u'description': u'A new digital assistant system, the first Persian AIML-based Chabot using Cased-Based Reasoning (CBR) available in (chatbot.ir)', u'title': u'First Persian AIML-based chabot'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2005.9 ~ 2011.1', u'description': u'Do you remember when a navigation device consisted of static instructions on a piece of paper and a multipage map? This is akin to learning resources and wikis based on text conveyed in successive pages and pictures. Our technology overcomes this limitation of wikis with the following features: \n1. Concept mapping construct so that pages and ideas are graphically arranged and customizable;\n2. Simplified Interactivity so that users can easily and quickly add videos, pictures, new links, comments, rankings, and more. \nWe leverage the power of crowds to enable learning methods as diverse as human beings\u2019 minds. Current wikis and online learning resources are not intuitive for humans. They do not combine visualization, collaboration, and interaction. One example of the need for this project is Wikipedia. It is among the 10 most visited websites. People crave dynamic, collaborative, interactive learning vehicles. \nMore specifically, this concept was implemented for three university courses previously. There was initial resistance, but the prototype won over the students and the teacher. Adoption skyrocketed over the course of a single academic term and the professor made it required reading in students' preparation for the final.', u'title': u'Science Tree: Adaptive Concept Mapping for Collaborative Knowledge Developing'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.9 ~ 2012.12', u'description': u'Team identified issues with communication practices for a local law library and made recommendations for future practice within the client organization. Analysis was made through interviews, interpretation sessions, and models of communication flow, along with the creation of an affinity wall to visualize this analysis.  Generated a final project plan that represented the team\u2019s findings and subsequent recommendations. ', u'title': u'SI 501: Suggestions for Improvement in Communication for Law Library'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2005.12 ~ 2012.12', u'description': u'The W3 was supposed to be an organized source of human knowledge which would be collaboratively developed by everyone from everywhere. In this project, disadvantages of hypertext and reasons preventing W3 from having a unified management to reach its goals are discussed and a collaborative system called 1Web solving disadvantages of hypertext is introduced; some of its applications are discussed, plus reasons showing how it helps W3 to reach its objectives. 1Web unifies, classifies and organizes the web contents by collaboration of all users and leads the web to be represented as a unified entity.', u'title': u'1Web: Systems and Methods for Collaborative Web Content Management and Visualization (filed for US Patent)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.1 ~ 2013.5', u'description': u'\u2022 Helping the developers understand the user experience of 3 \nmobile apps facilitating in-class collaboration\n\u2022 Conducted user interviews and surveys with 7th graders and \ngenerated research reports\n\u2022 Did task analysis and designed interaction map of 2 apps', u'title': u'Needs Assessment and Usability Evaluation - Intergalactic Mobile Learning Center'}]

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2014.11 ~ 2014.11', u'description': u'\u25cf Role: Graduate Student at Carnegie Mellon University\n\u25cf Course: Machine Learning(10601)\n\u25cf Brief: Designed a module in Python to model Hidden Markov Model. Implemented dynamic programming based Viterbi Algorithm in this module. \n\u25cf Description: User just needs to provide prior probabilities, transition probabilities and emission probabilities; he can obtain predictions like most likely hidden state sequence for given observed output sequence, probability of observing a sequence of output states, probability of observing a specific output given sequence of output states observed so far.\n\u25cf Using: Python\n', u'title': u'Hidden Markov Model for Predictions'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.12 ~ 2014.12', u'description': u'\u25cf Role: Graduate Student at Carnegie Mellon University\n\u25cf Course: Machine Learning(10601)\n\u25cf Brief: Designed and implemented a Recommendation Engine using Collaborative Filtering to predict user profile of a new user for set of products using memory based approach and make inferences for product recommendations.', u'title': u'Recommendation Engine using Collaborative Filtering'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.8 ~ 2014.12', u'description': u'\u25cf Role: Graduate Student at Carnegie Mellon University\n\u25cf Course: Cloud Computing (15619)\n\u25cf Brief: Developed system for analytics on Twitter dataset. \n\u25cf Designed and developed system using Amazon AWS's Elastic MapReduce clusters, Elastic Load Balancing, Apache Hadoop, Apache HBase, Autoscaling\n\u25cf Languages: Java and Go', u'title': u'Twitter Analytics Web Services'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.8 ~ 2015.5', u'description': u'I am working under Prof. William Cohen ( Machine Learning Department, School of Computer Science, Carnegie Mellon University) on a component in NELL(Never Ending Language Learner) ecosystem that extracts information from large scale natural language corpus using Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing algorithms, that will add to reasoning power of gloss free Knowledge Bases like NELL. ', u'title': u'Automatic Gloss Extraction from Large Scale Datasets like Wikipedia, ClueWeb09 and Wiktionary for Gloss free Knowledge Bases'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.9 ~ 2015.12', u'description': u'- Any dialog based Speech Recognition system like Amazon Echo or Google Now comes with a capability to understand what are you speaking or asking about. Basic Machine Learning challenges to enable that includes: intent prediction and slot detection.\n- Completed this project under Professor Ian Lane.\n- Given a spoken sentence my system can tell you the intent and corresponding slots in order to respond to query or spoken utterance\n- I designed and developed components for capability categorization and slot detection in a dialog based Speech Recognition system.\n- Capability categorization : The task is to categorize the spoken utterance based on which the dialog system can respond\n- Slot detection : The task is to detect the slots in spoken utterance based on which the dialog system can find entities in knowledge base and form appropriate response.\n- Used Maximum Entropy model for capability categorization and Conditional Random Fields for slot detection\n- Used Python', u'title': u'Automatic Slot Detection in Spoken Dialog Systems'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.11 ~ now', u'description': u'#Description: DevelopWeb is an Activity for Web Development using which children can develop Web Sites through HTML, Javascript and other web technologies. Children can learn quickly how to develop web pages in a step by step approach through examples provided for each HTML component.\n\n#Technologies: Python, GTK+, Sugar Desktop Environment, XO-1 Laptop', u'title': u'DevelopWeb : Web development IDE for OLPC XO laptops'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.10 ~ 2015.12', u'description': u'- Developed an Activity Recognition system using Artificial Neural Networks.\n- Goal is to recognize the daily activities performed by humans like eating, cooking, walking, riding, exercising, eating, driving,etc. based on sensor data.\n- Implemented Multi-layer Perceptron(MLP) network with different neuron activation functions( rectified linear unit, sigmoid, hyperbolic tangent) to recognize activity type using time series sensor data. \n- Achieved 87% 5-fold cross validation accuracy and 84% 80/20 train-test split accuracy.\n- Dataset used: Skoda Mini Checkpoint dataset\n\n\n', u'title': u'Activity Recognition using Recurrent Neural Networks'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.12 ~ 2014.12', u'description': u'\u25cf Role: Graduate Student at Carnegie Mellon University\n\u25cf Course: Cloud Computing (15619)\n\u25cf Brief: Designed and developed Input Text Prediction system by generating statistical language model using n-grams. It starts predicting what you are going to type based on what word you entered and give predicted words in Auto-complete as you get in Google Instant.\n\u25cf Designed and developed system using MapReduce paradigm on Apache Hadoop and Apache HBase\n\u25cf Programming Language: Java', u'title': u'Input Text Predictor using Statistical Language Modeling'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.11 ~ 2014.12', u'description': u'\u25cf Role: Graduate Student at Carnegie Mellon University\n\u25cf Course: Machine Learning(10601)\n\u25cf Brief: Developed a system for object recognition in images from CIFAR-10 image collection.\n\u25cf Description: Implemented Unsupervised feature learning framework for feature space transformation, convolutional feature extraction methods and classification', u'title': u'Object Recognition using Unsupervised Feature Learning'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.5 ~ now', u'description': u'#Description: Developed a intuitive utility for high speed data synchronization, metadata synchronization,mirror replication of Salesforce.com cloud environments.\n\n#Technologies: VB.Net, Salesforce.com's Force.com cloud platform(PaaS), Synchronization Algorithms on Windows', u'title': u'Pipes: Sync your Salesforce Clouds in flash with clicks'}]

summary: I'm a Silicon Valley-based entrepreneur, author, executive, and investor.\n\nI'm coauthor of the New York Times bestselling management book The Alliance: Managing Talent in the Networked Age (with LinkedIn chairman Reid Hoffman and entrepreneur Chris Yeh). I'm also coauthor of the New York Times bestselling career strategy book The Start-Up of You: Adapt to the Future, Invest in Yourself, and Transform Your Career (with Reid Hoffman).\n\nAs entrepreneur and executive, I've started and scaled several ventures, including an e-government software company (Comcate) that currently delivers hosted CRM solutions to hundreds of local governments in America, an online education business, and a top tier boutique management training business.\n\nRecently, I helped conceive, then built up and ran a new organization to amplify and extend Reid Hoffman’s strategic priorities. I worked out of the LinkedIn and Greylock Partners offices for two years. Lessons learned here: http://www.casnocha.com/Reid-Hoffman-lessons \n\nAs an angel investor, I have financed and incubated various tech businesses in Silicon Valley. I try to add value by helping CEOs with their top talent/people challenges.\n\nFinally, I regularly deliver keynote speeches on business and globalization. I've spoken in a dozen countries in front of tens of thousands of people. I've appeared on the CBS Early Show, CNN, Charlie Rose, CNBC, and other media outlets.

summary: As a creative services professional for many years, I have worked as a graphic designer, creative services director, circulation manager, editor, writer and VP-Operations in publishing, advertising and higher education. summary: Knowledge management is about collecting, curating, presenting, and preserving the stories we tell about our work and our lives for the benefit of our team. Social media and cloud computing provide unprecedented ways for us to manage these stories across organizational, class, cultural, and geographic boundaries--that's where I come in. \n\nI can help your team:\n+ learn what it already knows\n+ preserve what it learns\n+ present what it knows in a way that best benefits its personnel, customers, and the world\n\nChange in my own career parallels the struggles of companies as they deal with cultural (diversity along all dimensions--race, gender, cultural, language, thought, decision and development methodologies, etc.) and technological disruptions (the Internet of Things, Sensors, cloud computing, open source systems, wireless systems, energy transfer and storage, maker/tinkerer communities).  \n\nThe titles have changed--systems engineer to technical writer to technical communicator to analyst to knowledge manager--but my focus (indeed, my JOY) has always been with helping teams know what they know and share what they know.\n\nSpecialties:  dialogic pedagogy, cafe and workshop training, technical communication, systems engineering (peer project management), holistic cyber security, wireless systems, project scaffolding, intellectual property, networks, Linux,  cloud and crowd-source content development.\n\nCore value: The Golden Rule. I'm only willing to work with people who know what this rule is, believe it, and are willing to work within its constraints.

summary: •\t9+ years of in-depth experience in Data Architecture, Database Administration including Oracle (11g/10g/9i) on platforms Aix, Sun Solaris, Unix/Linux & windows,SQL Server 2005/2008.\n•\tBuild and Configure Oracle 11g R2 RAC on multiple nodes clusters. \n•\tHands on Experience in Performance tuning & optimization using DBMS_STATS, optimizer hint and tools like Explain Plan, STATSPACK, Index re-organization, SQL Trace, SQL Profiles, TKPROF. Analyzed ASH, AWR & ADDM reports.\n•\tWorked on setting up Physical and Logical standby Data Guard Environments.\n•\tInstalled and applied CPU/PSU patches to oracle RDBMS.\n•\tDatabase Upgradation, Migrations using traditional way (DBUA, Manual & export/import) as well as non-traditional way (Transportable tablespaces) and SQL Tuning Advisor, Flashback Table, Tablespace Management.\n•\tHands on experience in Backup, Recovery & Cloning of databases using RMAN.\n•\tExperience to implement and configuration Oracle DB vault and audit vault.\n•\tExperience in GoldenGate 10x, 11.1 implementation, Upgradation, Performance tuning GoldenGate extract and Replicats processes for real time database replication. \n•\tExperience in Transportable Tablespaces, Materialized Views.\n•\tExperience in 11g grid control and 12c cloud control.\n•\tData movement (import/export, data pump, SQL*Loader).\n•\tExperience to write Optimal SQL Query, PL/SQL and T-SQL Scripting.\n•\tWorked on creating and Managing Users, Roles and Privilege.\n•\tExperience with very large database.\n•\tETL, Pentaho, Data Warehousing Dimensional Modeling. Cube, Rollup Query. \n•\tHandling tools such as TOAD, SQL*Advantage and OEM.\n•\tUNIX/LINUX installation and shell scripting.\n•\tImplement and Maintain SQL Server 2005/2008 and HA (Replication, Log Shipping, Mirroring & Cluster).\n•\tWorked With Oracle Global Customer Support Service Request (SR) Analyst\n\nSpecialties: \n\nOracle 9i/10g/11g/12c Database, RAC, Data Guard, Goldengate, Enterprise Manager (EM) Grid Control, RMAN, Upgrades, Migrations, Performance Tuning.

summary: Working as a developer on contract at Gilead Sciences, Foster City since January 2014. projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2005.8 ~ 2005.8', u'description': u'It is a complete package, built in Oracle Forms and Reports having all the HRMS required features.\t\n\u25e6\tDeveloped Oracle Forms and Reports in 10g.\n\u25e6\tResponsible for developing the Oracle Packages and Reports.\n\u25e6\tInvolved in DBA Activities as well.\n\u25e6\tEstablish Quality Procedures and continuously monitor and audit to ensure the deliverable meets quality goals.\n', u'title': u'Human Resource Management System (HRMS)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2010.5 ~ now', u'description': u'Sales Station would serve as a robust Enterprise Compensation & Performance Management tool that will enable consistent approach to managing the sales process across Asia Pacific. It would support multiple business Segment sales organization and serve as a platform for reliable & timely sales information by aiding in Goal setting, measurement & incentive calculation across the sales hierarchy. This will help in development of healthy sales culture for rewards & recognition. KPI definition module brings the ability of configuring new and existing KPIs to the users directly, by reducing time and effort significantly spent on introducing changes to KPIs.\nIt has below features\n\uf0f1\t\u201cGoal Allocation\u201d aides in setting a goal for a KPI for a user or a set of users in a single shot while addressing the grace on the goals for special cases. The interactive interface makes the goal allocation simple and effective\n\uf0f1\tScheme Wizard uses one of the best Rule Engines to simplify changes and introduction of new schemes. It uses \u201cRete algorithm\u201d to compute the schemes in a bulk there by saving time and CPU during computation. The user friendly interface makes the scheme maintenance easy for any user to maintain the scheme\n\uf0f1\t\u201cSimulation of schemes\u201d, which can be used for the biz planning exercise, provides business the flexibility to simulate new schemes before introduction into main stream with existing or new set of data\n\uf0f1\tMicro marketing a powerful analytical tool enables analysis on the customer data by cutting them through different dimensions available in SS and gauging them with the KPIs. This is one of the tools to generate leads and send to COPS. Leads generated for various biz segments and channels will complement the COPS generated data.\n', u'title': u'sales station'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.6 ~ 2011.6', u'description': u'ACES  is a single platform provide management insights covering daily sales, balance, profitability, net flow; sales force productive and cross sell performance across Asia Pacific region. It has regional sales dashboard/ data mart, leveraging on existing Enterprise Warehouse (EDW), Sales station and Financial Data Warehouse (FDW). It is a single Platform for standardizing KPI definitions for consistent analysis & decision making across region. Provide daily business matrix across 15 AP countries, product, customer segments and sales hierarchy on daily bases through a set of KPIs \u2013 useful for analyzing business trend & variations from Plan numbers.\nTarget User Groups in Regional and 15 Countries\n\uf0f1\tRegional Sales \n\uf0f1\tProduct segments SMEs (Subject Matter Experts)\n\uf0f1\tRegional Heads\n\uf0f1\tFINCON\n\uf0f1\tDM- country Business & function Heads\nRole and Responsibility\n\u25e6\tPL/SQL development (packages, procedures, Scripts, functions and triggers).\n\u25e6\tOracle Forms/Reports Development.\n\u25e6\tPerform business gathering requirements from business users, stakeholders, and Subject Matter Experts (SME\u2019s) \n\u25e6\tResponsible for requirements and design phases.\n\u25e6\tDeveloped a layer to close the gap between DRI and Rainbow.\n\u25e6\tGather requirements and write specification and functional design documents for software development.\n', u'title': u'Asia Consumer Enterprise Solution (ACES)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2007.1 ~ 2007.1', u'description': u'Involved with communicating clients and the backend programming by creating packages, procedures, Export/Import Database, optimize queries and DBA Related task in production environment.\nResponsible to gather requirement and provides Schedule and Ad hoc reports.\n\nDRP- Before write off Identify the potential customer not paying Outstanding. Bank can collect a minimum required amount and make installments for the rest amount. It will take care of closing all old accounts and creating a new account and track the account up to complete amount received. Not less than 50 people are using this package and continuously log the required improvement activities in the Lotus notes and after getting the approval. Senior management will have regular reviews of the progress and direct oversight of the changes made to the solution, and constant reporting on current user requests, interfaces monitoring, etc. \nIdentify the Customer where Risk Involved. summary: I'm a Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES) techno-functional IT professional possessing 7 and 1/2 years of experience, having been primarily involved in MES application development, support, integration and maintenance for hi-tech, automotive and pharmaceutical/biotech companies.\n\nMES product experience has been mainly on the Rockwell Factory Talk Production Centre Suite, Apriso Flexnet 9.5/9.6 and Emerson Syncade / Delta V platforms.\n\nDevelopment/Support experience has encompassed working with core Java, JavaScript, VBScript, PL/SQL, SQL, T-SQL, Oracle and SQL Server Database versions. Also possess basic knowledge of TIBCO as an MES - ERP integration platform, along with awareness on developing PLSQL based Web Services on the JDeveloper tool.\n\nExperience garnered as MES Track Lead for HCL supporting multiple client installations under the aegis of a Managed Services Engagement has led to competent absorption of the tenets of ITIL based Incident/Change/Problem/Release Management practices while delivering daily activities, proper understanding of Service Level Agreements and adherence to the same while working on support/service request response and resolution, as well as efficient stakeholder operational status reporting method incorporation.\n\nPreparation of requirements specification/functional specification documents while participating in workshops with customer Manufacturing/Engineering/Quality/IT groups has enabled greater understanding of business needs and how elucidated requirements can impact the efficiency of the overall supply chain process. Also experienced in deployment of enhanced objects/artifacts through stages of non-Production functional/regression/user acceptance testing cycles leading up to final implementation on Production environment.\n

It is difficult to change system calls, either globally or on a per process basis. Having different system calls per\nprocess is useful for various scenarios. summary: TL; DR: GOOG, GCP, SA, SD, OFA, NASA, xAWS, xVT, xRT, JS, Bb, OMG, BBQ!\n\nI'm delivering the value of cloud computing to startups, agencies, ISV's, and enterprises so they can stop wasting time with infrastructure and start accelerating their businesses. When I learned the elegance of relational algebra and the power of SQL, I started to focus on relational databases.\n\nI prefer to stay consistently challenged in my professional career. summary: Scalable distributed systems architect and developer. Highly experienced with\ndatabase kernel engineering, building massively parallel processing systems,\ndesigning for maximum scalability, identifying and resolving performance\nbottlenecks. Major contributor in PostgreSQL project. Author of Ordered Set\nAggregates feature and Grouping Sets feature in PostgreSQL. Author of many\nmajor performance patches for PostgreSQL. Inventor of three distributed\nsystems algorithms targeted at improving scalability and on the fly load\nmanagement. Filed many patents in database kernel engineering domain.\n\n\nWorking on improving scalable analytics in PostgreSQL. Also engaged in\nimproving write scalability and scalable transaction management in\nRethinkDB, a new generation NoSQL analytical database.\n\nCurrently authoring a book on RethinkDB and distributed databases for Packt\nPublishing and evaluating an offer for a book on building scalable distributed\nsystems from Springer.

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2012.6 ~ now', u'description': u'With 30 years experience in the pensions industry, I offer inspirational one-day Retirement Awareness Workshops to small groups (between 6 and 20 delegates). \n\nRetirement is the major milestone in our lives when key questions of identity and purpose arise.\n\nThese workshops are interactive and hugely enjoyable - covering all aspects of retirement: emotional/psychological; health & well-being; occupational; and financial issues. \n\nOur seminars  are an ideal way for employers to prepare their staff  (of any age) for the challenges that retirement brings.  \n\nAlternatively, if you are approaching retirement and feel lacking in direction, this course will give you the inspiration you are seeking to start on this next exciting phase of your life's journey.\n\nWe're never too young - nor too old - to consider our life plan.\n \nContact Pam Jenkinson at info@3RO.co.uk or on \n07599 765 915 for details regarding availability.', u'title': u'Retirement Awareness Workshops'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.7 ~ now', u'description': u'These one day workshops are ideal for anyone at a crossroads, e.g. approaching retirement, redundancy or a career change.  Major changes in our lives produce challenges to our understanding of who we are, our role, and our purpose.  Our one day interactive course will tailored to your own requirements by ascertaining before-hand from all participants what you wish us to cover (via our pre-course questionnaire).  \n\nOur aim is to inspire you to approach the next chapter of your life proactively and equip you to continue your exploration independently after the course ends.  \n\nView our web-site (www.3ro.co.uk) for further details or simply contact Pam.', u'title': u'\'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.4 ~ 2014.4', u'description': u'Is your pet causing you stress?\n\nOur pets can sense our emotions and will react to us.  If you become stressed, frustrated or lose your temper this can set up a loop of negative behaviour - in them and in you.\n\nWe can assist you to react positively and stay in control of the situation.  This will enable you to establish and maintain a positive and loving relationship with your pet. \n', u'title': u'Coaching for Pet Owners'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.6 ~ 2016.6', u'description': u'Subject:  Managing to be the Best PA:  Career, Personal development and Work/Life Balance\n@aces_pa\nA lovely day on 10th June.  RZSS venue.  Fabulous delegates!', u'title': u'Speaker at the 9th Annual Conference and Award for Executive Secretaries and PAs in Scotland'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.11 ~ 2014.11', u'description': u'3RO offers an open invitation to anyone who would like to join us on our monthly walks.  Enjoy beautiful scenery, whilst taking gentle exercise and fresh air, with friends.  All that's required is sensible shoes and appropriate clothing, bearing in mind our changeable Scottish climate, and a respect for everyone's own map of the world.\nWe usually end up somewhere restful for a coffee, and perhaps cake.\nCheck our web-site for the date and location for our next walk.\nWe'd love to have your company.', u'title': u'3RO Armadillo Walks'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.5 ~ 2014.7', u'description': u'Involved in actions and strategies, handling complaints raised by customers.  Made daily use of a complex combination of systems:  RESOLVE, PEGA, Witness, Main Frame and  Microsoft Office with the aim of resolving issues as swiftly and fully as possible, within regulatory time-frames.', u'title': u'Short-term contract with Scottish Widows/Lloyds'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.2 ~ 2015.10', u'description': u'Investigating complaints within the Customer Relations Unit.  Working with various software:  Microsoft Office,Lotus Notes, 4Front, Work-Smart, Verint, and the company's own main frame, to provide solutions as swiftly as possible, and within regulatory time-scales.', u'title': u'Short-term contract with Capita Remediation Services for Prudential in Stirling'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2017.3 ~ 2017.4', u'description': u'3RO \u2013 April Success.  \u201cOne Day\u201d or \u201cDay 1\u201d?\n\nOur dreams and aspirations for \u201cone-day\u201d will remain unrealised, unless we make a conscious commitment to make them happen.\n\nJoin me on 20 March 2017 for \u201cDay One\u201d of our journey to \u201cApril Success\u201d.\n\nChoose a short-term, high impact goal that you have procrastinated over.  In the six weeks between 20 March and 30 April we will blitz our goals together.\n\nJoin my 3RO \u2013 April Success Facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/groups/1372435382816816/) for encouragement and inspirations.\n\nAnd if you feel your resolve weakening at any point, share your thoughts and the group will provide a listening ear and support to get you back on track.\n\nIt\u2019s free. It\u2019s friendly. And you will feel fabulous on 30 April when you have finally nailed that goal.\n\nI have already shared my goal on the group page, and posted the first of many tools to help you on your journey.', u'title': u'3RO - April Success'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.9 ~ 2016.9', u'description': u'With effect from 1 September 2016, we are offering a new concept in life-coaching.   \n\nOur 3RO Holiday-Pods will provide you with your own personal oasis of calm, positively-focused time and space.  \n\nThe Holiday-Pod is a series of coaching sessions constructed to give you the same re-energised feeling and spring in your step that an ideal holiday would have provided for you.  The advantages of the Holiday-Pod are that it is: \n\n-          cost-effective (cheaper than a holiday);\n\n-          fully focused on you;  \n\n-          you can choose the timing of your sessions; and \n\n-          you can, if you wish, be coached by Skype in the comfort of your own home.\n\nThere is no standard format to a Holiday-Pod.  We will structure your Holiday-Pod to meet your needs.  You are unique, and that means we will provide a unique service to give you the results you desire.  Perhaps you wish to feel calm; confident; in control; or to focus on one or a series of specific issues.   Maybe you would like to prepare for a forthcoming annual work review, or consider a new career path.  The choice is yours.\n\nThe three main principles underlying this coaching concept are:\n\n1. Positive-Focus\n\n2. Outcome\n\n3 .Directed-Action\n\nContact Pam at info@3ro.co.uk to find out more.\n\n', u'title': u'Life-Coaching Holiday-Pods'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.1 ~ 2016.1', u'description': u'It's fun to buy stuff.  New clothes, or items for our homes, but do you let something old go when something new arrives?  Or are you accumulating clutter?\n\nOur \', u'title': u'Positive-Space Coaching'}]

summary: I am a certified Facilitator, Master Practitioner of NLP (Neuro Linguist Programming), and certified Teacher of English as a Foreign Language.\n\nAfter over 30 years working in the UK pensions industry, I was inspired to establish 3RO Ltd to communicate the importance of  a holistic approach to retirement , i.e. raise awareness of the crucial psychological, and physiological aspects which are often overlooked by financial advisers.  \n\nMy focus has since broadened, and I have assisted clients in a broad range of life-transitions and changes.  I help clients to clarify their aims and achieve their goals.\n\nIn 2017 I gained my TEFL certification which enables me to teach English as a Foreign Language. summary: I qualified as a French avocat in 2014 with an already established pedigree in the international maritime world. Fluent in both English and Spanish, having studied and worked in both these countries, I am also an accomplished transatlantic sailor. \n\nPrior to qualification I worked at the French maritime authority, “Affaires Maritime” and spent 2 years working with Thomas Cooper’s Paris office leading up to my qualification in 2014.  \n\nIn addition to my legal expertise, my sailing experience allows me to offer in-depth technical knowledge of pleasure and racing yachting, and I am regularly involved in yachting and super yachting matters in France, including court surveyor investigations, covering such matters as fires, dismastings, keel and other ship/yacht building issues for owners, yards, architects and naval engineers. \n\nIn yacht racing I had represented teams participating in the Route du Rhum, Jacques Vabre and the Vendée Globe amongst others.  \n\nMy experience also encompasses maritime personal injury, both crew and passenger claims, for large cruise operators. \n\nI am also frequently involved in sea, fluvial, road and rail carriage disputes as well as casualties involving salvage and collisions.  Finally I am regularly involved in ship arrests and other conservatory proceedings in France.\n

summary: I have 25 years experience in software architecture and product development, including 9 years in startups. I built 4 products from scratch. I managed international distributed teams (80 people in US, Europe, India, and China). I successfully outsourced product development to India (Bangalore and Noida). I am an EDA expert, and I brought innovations in formal verification, logic synthesis, physical synthesis, and combinatorial optimization. More recently I designed solutions for a wide spectrum of applications, from search engines for e-business, to cloud computing platforms, to massively parallel logic simulation.\n\nSpecialties: \n- problem solving, complex system design, memory and runtime optimization\n- software architecture & algorithms (C/C++ expert)\n- EDA (RTL/logic/physical synthesis, simulation, low power, formal verification, etc)\n- software engineering & team management\n- cloud computing (AWS, virtual platforms, security)\n\nCheck my blog (http://www.ocoudert.com/blog/) and publications (http://www.ocoudert.com/blog/publications/).

summary: Founder and CEO of Concurrent EDA\nMy company has created design automation tools that analyze and convert software into FPGA devices.  We offer fixed-fee analysis and design services and work with a number of FPGA platforms.  See www.ConcurrentEDA.com for more information.\n\nPrior life was as an assistant professor at University of Pittsburgh in the Dept. of Electrical and Computer Engineering.  I researched and created high-performance  architectures with a focus on FPGA-acceleration and high-level synthesis.  50 publications later, I ran out of ink and started Concurrent EDA.  I have kept my teaching going but only teach a graduate class on FPGA Hardware Design in the evenings.  (ECE 2120)\n\nFormer-former life was at Purdue where I earned my Ph.D. in \nElectrical and Computer Engineering.  This is were I cut my teeth on FPGAs (Altera Flex 20K) and had to manually synthesize my VHDL into gates because the tools were sub-optimal.  This started my obsession into FPGAs.  My thesis was rapid synchronization and collective operations in the FPGA-based network.\n\nSpecialties: FPGA design (Xilinx, Altera, Lattice, Actel)\nAcceleration of software using FPGAs\nFPGA Design Automation Tool Design\nHigh performance embedded systems\nLabVIEW FPGA Designs in VHDL or LV FPGA

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'', u'description': u'The OpenPDK Coalition was founded in mid-2010 with the goal of defining a set of open standards to allow an OpenPDK to be created once and then translated into specific EDA vendor tools and specific foundry formats. This will allow an OpenPDK to be as portable across foundries and as agnostic to EDA tools as possible. The Si2 OpenPDK standard will enable greater efficiency in PDK development, verification, and delivery. summary: Here is a list of problems I am solving these days in no particular order: \n\n* IP design for Server SoC: I manage a great team of chip designers and build a key server building block for Intel server (Xeon). \n* Machine learning: I feel very passionate about learning, teaching and applying various machine learning concepts ranging from fundamental theory to application (mainly to chip design and verification). \n* Python: Love so many things I can do with it. I teach children how to code using Python. I also write quite a bit of programs for work as well as hobby. For work, I do some file processing, ETL (Extract, Transform and Load) and indicator generation using numpy, pandas and other modules. \n* Continuous Integration: I manage a busy pipeline for our RTL source code which runs a large number of tests and deal with many issues that come with being a gate keeper. \n* Teaching: I used to teach at Berkeley (MBA) and San Jose State (Computer Architecture). Still want to get back into it at some point\n* Memory: I am just a fan of the industry at this point, love hearing and learning about new things in DRAM, NAND and other forms of memory.\n

summary: Workplace Violence is prevalent in Healthcare and Social Service environments- but it doesn't have to be tolerated (from co-workers, patients, customers, and others).  We help your people to be and feel safe so they can focus and build stronger teams and offer better customer service.  \n\nBe sure you have the optimum Violence Prevention Program and avoid lawsuits, customer complaints (public and private), and team turnover.\n\nOrganizations bring in Empowered when any of the following applies: \n•You serve the public, and experience interactions with angry or unreasonable customers.\n•Managers feel like babysitters, and staff feel micro-managed.\n•Assertive communication is avoided in favor of gossip, cliques, and silos. \n•You have a variety of genders, cultures, and generations working together.\n•Frustrations abound, and your best employees are updating their resumes. \n•Your Violence Prevention Program may not be effective at protecting you from lawsuits.\n\nmore info at www.EmpoweredFACTS.com

Vojtech Juranek lead it together with Lucie Vot\xfdpkov\xe1 from the JBoss side.', u'title': u'Integrating Jenkins CI with Kerberos'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.4 ~ 2012.1', u'description': u'Huge pile of work was done by Mladen, see his blog:\nhttp://www.syndicateofideas.com/posts/fighting-the-msvcrt-dll-hell\nhttp://www.syndicateofideas.com/posts/making-of-jboss-enterprise-web-server\nUpstream project of Brew (RH build system) we were migrating windows builds to is called Koji: http://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Koji\n', u'title': u'Leading migration to a new build system for windows native builds of JBoss EAP/EWP/EWS'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.9 ~ 2015.9', u'description': u'I am responsible for productization of EAP 6.x CP stream product and represent our team at PM table. CP streams are security & customer case driven releases of our core Middleware product.', u'title': u'Product Lead for EAP 6.x. Cummulative Patch (CP) Stream'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.3 ~ 2011.6', u'description': u'Creating modular architecture for EAP/EWP Continuous integration using Jenkins CI. summary: Robert Sher is founding principal of CEO to CEO, a consulting firm of former chief executives that improves the leadership infrastructure of midsized companies seeking to accelerate their performance.   \n\nRobert has published extensively on the successful leadership traits of CEOs of mid-market companies. He has written two books, Mighty Midsized Companies; How Leaders Overcome 7 Silent Growth Killers (Bibliomotion, Sep. 2014) and, The Feel of the Deal (1oPonder, 2007) and is a regular columnist for the online version of Forbes and CFO Magazine. He also publishes his own newsletter, The CEO Insomnia Factor.\n\nCEO to CEO has worked with chief executives of such companies as GoGrid (a fast-growing and pioneering cloud computing firm), Rodan + Fields (a fast-growing $200MM revenue skin care company), Cellairis (an Atlanta based franchisor of wireless accessories-750 locations), Babette (a women's clothing manufacturer and retailer-8 stores) and Hanson Bridgett LLP (a San Francisco-based law firm-400 people).\n\nCEO to CEO elevates the skills of successful CEOs and their teams who lead midsized companies. We help these executives improve their capabilities in three areas: leadership skills (including defining and maintaining a high performance corporate culture); business skills (e.g., competitive analysis and planning); and interpersonal skills (e.g., managing relationships with investors, board directors, and the management team).\n\nUnlike consulting firms that are brought in to solve company problems, we are former CEOs of mid-market companies who equip those in the C Suite with the skills to address those problems. And while executive coaches largely help leaders improve their interpersonal skills, we develop business acumen and leadership acumen in addition to personal acumen. Lastly, where university programs teach executives in classrooms, we bring the education to our clients so they can use their new skills to solve pressing issues.\n\nSpecialties: Midmarket businesses\nCEO Coaching\nTop Line Growth\nBusiness Planning\t\nStrategy Development\t\nM&A\nSuccession\t\nFund Raising\t\nManaging the Board\t\nOrganizational Structure\t\nGovernance\t\nFinancial Performance\t\nTop Team Development\nHigh Performance Environment\t\nExecutive communications\t\nMeeting Facilitation & Offsites\t\nCulture & Morale\t\nEmotional Intelligence\t\nMentoring Leaders\t\nDeliberate Visibility\t\nAssertiveness\t\nFamily Business

summary: I'm a Coaching Psychologist with 30 years commercial experience gained in global organisations and small to medium enterprises. I work at depth with people who are interested in exploring their inner worlds to create transformational change in their work and personal lives. My clients are people who are working on their own development and I support them in becoming more of what they want to be. \n\n• Coaching for success includes work goal areas such as leadership development, career transition, resilience, entrepreneurship, expansion, legacy and retirement planning.\n• Coaching for fulfilment increases feelings of wellbeing and happiness, provides resources for self-regulation and stress management, and leads to better relationships and greater work-life balance.\n• Integrative coaching allows clients to work with both these goal areas simultaneously, in a whole person approach to change.\n• Developing mindfulness supports clients to non-judgmentally attend to values and the role their feelings play in your inner world, and how these impact thinking and relationships.\n\nI help leaders connect with their authentic voice and sense of potency within organisational contexts. This involves developing resilience to sustain and support through challenging events and resistance to change, and strengthening in adaptability and self-belief. Inner critic work and impostor phenomenon feelings are particular areas of interest; helping clients identify ways they may unconsciously sabotage success, and finding adaptive and effective ways to work with defences.\n\nQualifications:\nBSc Psychology (First Class Hons) Open University \nMSc Coaching Psychology, Metanoia Institute (awarded Distinction for dissertation)\n\nMemberships:\nBPS, SGCP\nAPECS\nAssociation for Coaching\nAccredited Senior Practitioner, Metanoia Institute\n\nSpecialist areas: \nCareer transition, relationships, work-life balance, stress management, parts work\nTrauma treatment \nImpostor Syndrome\nMindfulness

summary: I am a Certified Assertiveness Coach certified by Hay House.  I am also an educator and certified mediator.  I create interactive online courses and provide consulting services for assertiveness, teacher mentoring, integration of spiritual principle in daily life, work-life balance, meaningful career solutions, negotiation, adult education, online media, and building practical cooperation skills based on spiritual principle and prayer. \n\nMy educational background includes a Master of Science degree in Training Systems from the University of Central Arkansas; a Graduate Certificate in Mediation from the University of Arkansas at Little Rock, including the William H. Bowen School of Law, the Clinton School of Public Service, and the UALR School of Social Work; and a Graduate Certificate in Management from the UALR School of Business.  Coursework from these programs and my professional experience include instructional design, online course creation, online teaching, training delivery, coaching for the workplace, adult education and learning theory, seminar design, facilitation of classes and seminars for adult learners, and online seminar management.  My mediation education includes the mediation of family, civil, and business agreements, negotiation, business communication skills, and designing alternative dispute resolution systems.  My management education and experience include human resources, online marketing skills, and team leadership.

summary: Tom is a psychologist, actor, educator, and author of Full Heart Living: Conversations with the Happiest People I Know. Licensed as a Psychologist in 1991, he has provided integrative, person-centered individual, couples, and group counseling and therapy since 1986.  He received his Masters degree in Community Counseling from Minnesota State University in Mankato, MN.  \n\nIn addition to his Tuesday night Group for Men and Women, Tom sees clients individually, supervises mental health professionals, and teaches classes on many topics, including assertiveness, reducing anxiety, handling change, and optimism.  His most recent class, Your Happiness Project, combines elements from some of his favorites: Positive Psychology, Emotional Intelligence, Resilience Theory, Mindfulness Training, and more. \n\nTom also acts on stage, in films, in commercials, and has appeared in print ads and appears on AM950's wellness show, The Wake Up Call many Saturday mornings.\n\nSpecialties: Anxiety, Post Traumatic Stress Disorder, Depression, Family Issues, Transitions, Intimacy, Group Psychotherapy, Sexuality

There is nothing a computer cannot do that money and time cannot buy.\n2.)  Every challenge brings with it an underlying opportunity.\n3.)  Early adoption of new ideas means you have to Accept, Adapt and Adopt to be competitive.\n\nMy clients agree.\n\nThe Company\n\nSmartfinds is a digital marketing agency working with national and global corporate clients including domestic and off-shore franchise operations with their online marketing efforts.
