summary: Kellies professional experience in therapeutic person centred settings in the public (community) & private sectors extends over 26 years.  \n\nRecognised at 18 as a recipient of The Rotary Youth Leadership Award Kellie's filled a variety of  leadership roles inc: \n\nTeaching & Mentoring in Natural Beauty & Wellness @ CSTT; \n\nAs an Allied Health Practitioner /Therapies Coordinator/ Team Leader & Mentor within the Hospital system promoting Well being through Lifestyle & Psycho-social Interventions. \n\nKellie led the team through innovative change achieving excellence in accreditation & recognition nationally by the Aged Care Channel. \n\nDeveloped & facilitated extensive person centred therapies & holistic programs meeting the complex integral health needs of a diverse population across 3 campuses for a decade full time.  \n\nAnd oversaw Community Development programs inc:  innovative Inter-generational therapies to enhance quality of life recieving further recognition. \n\nQualifications Inc: \nDiversional Therapist,\nAllied Health & Lifestyle Practitioner, \nDip. Leisure & Health, \nMaster Coach. \nBach. in Applied Social Science minoring in Coaching.\n\nCompleted units inc: \nCareer Counselling,  \nPsychology of Health & Wellness, \nOrganizational Behavior (Motivation & Performance)\nPositive Psych\nDevelopmental Psych\nCounselling Intensives 1 & 2, \nMental Health (Recovery)\nMajor Sociology: Systems, Policy & Analysis.. \nCoaching minor\n@ACAP\n(For more: Ref: Ed. section). \n\nKellie's deeply committed to providing best practice developing her professional integrity,  knowledge, research skills & methods.\n\nAs an experienced Coach, Therapist &  Counsellor Kellie Founded 'Courage to Flourish' a Lifestyle Wellness practice empowering individuals to improve the quality of their life.\n\nAlso a Founding Facilitator @The Inspiration Formula; a Style Coach & The Lifestyle Chic.\n\nKellie provides successful outcomes  backed by her professional experience & evidence based science.\n\n\n\n

summary: Helping to create the greatest net positive impact on this planet in the shortest amount of time, this is the professional goal that I am pursuing. Why? I believe to have ways of getting there, and I am concerned with the direction that we´re taking our planet, a place which I dearly love. \n\nI am passionate about sustainability. I started to specialize in it in 1995. My experience of working closely with many talented people in this field, including eco-gurus such as William McDonough (author of Cradle to Cradle and pioneer in the circular economy), participating in projects with tiny budgets as well as multi million budgets for corporate or institutional clients (IBM, Ford, GAP,...), starting two companies focused on sustainability ...all combined has made me learn about sustainability in a broad way and appreciate it from multiple angles. \n\nHaving lived in 8 countries (and worked for projects in many more), made me to see first hand how individuals, companies, cities and regions can implement an extensive number of solutions (practices, technologies...) that create ecological, social and economical benefit. I also got to appreciate how culture and education play an important role.\n\nGetting an insight into understanding some of the main triggers that help either promote or block sustainable development at a micro and macro scale, along with my team, we have developed digital platforms designed to help citizens, corporations/organizations, cities and regions spread and implement sustainability. Our platforms help to measure, benchmark, find applicable solutions and promote their adoption and the engagement with the stakeholder.\nThis all translates into optimizing energy and water consumption, improving waste management as well as social practices, etc., which in turn leads to individuals, companies, cities... to save money, reduce CO2 emissions and improve their reputation, among many more benefits.\n\nAlways open to connect with other Linkedin users.

summary: My philosophy:\n•  What I focus the most is the ability to learn and adapt fast. The world is moving at a very fast way, and we need to keep up. Whatever you learn today might be obsolete, years from now... so keep learning!\n\n•  Autonomy, adaptability, resilience, and perseverance are the four pillars in which I stand, in that order. Autonomy helps me to be an autodidact and have the self-discipline to teach myself things I never did before. Adaptability helps me to switch gears as the world changes and use my autonomy to learn new things. Resilience helps me to get up when I feel I am falling and recover with stamina. And perseverance helps me to keep marching forward!\n\nContinuous Education:\n•  Microsoft, Professional Program Certificate in Data Science | Professional Certificate - In progress\n•  Udacity, Data Analyst | Nanodegree - In progress\n

summary: For over 25 years I've been actively involved in personal development as a corporate trainer, an educator in continuing education, a strategy coach and as a student of continuous learning. My training focuses both on personal and career development.\n\nMy clients discover from my tele-classes, webinars, mastermind programs and group coaching how to focus on their strengths and develop winning strategies to get the results they are looking for.\n\nPrivate Coaching\n\nI combine my professional experience, my training as a certified Master Coach, and my life experience and work with one-on-one with individuals in private coaching sessions. I believe that we all have the answers within ourselves and I want everyone to realize their potential to live powerful, rewarding lives.\nWorking with a Strategy Coach gives you a framework to think bigger thoughts. summary: I'm a board certified, licensed clinical psychologist in private practice on Colorado Boulevard in Pasadena, California where I work with adults on a variety of emotional, relational, spiritual and existential issues. I write for two magazines to a global audience to demystify psychology and therapy. I have supervised and taught psychology graduate students. I also apply my clinical and writing skills to internet startups, I formed a psychotherapy awareness day, and developed and launched a mental health checkup protocol. In my spare time I play guitar in a rock band and make the world's best tomato sauce each and every weekend.\n\nClinical Specialties: Board Certified in Clinical Psychology by the American Board of Professional Psychology (ABPP). My work typically includes depression, anxiety, relationships, men's issues, concerns with purpose or the meaning of life, and creativity and other work-related issues.\n\nWriting Specialities: Psychotherapy, transference, termination, forgiveness, shame, reconciliation, assertiveness, clinical supervision, personality, finance, therapist professional development, and all aspects of the therapist-client relationship.

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2016.8 ~ 2016.12', u'description': u'We are working cohesively with members of the VTA to analyze commuting trends in the Santa Clara Bay Area to accumulate data that can help VTA restructure and reorganize its current routes. We hope that we can encourage more users to take advantage of the services provided by the VTA. After researching commuting behavior from various outlets such as schools, cities, companies, government, and surveys, we wrote Python Scripts for the data sets that were most applicable for our project. Github was utilized throughout this project to help us monitor, organize, and present deliverables. Most of the communication for this project was done through a tool called Slack. We constantly keep in contact with our VTA project sponsors and incorporated a Gantt Chart to track weekly progress. After gathering the appropriate data, we presented the results with the assistance of Microsoft Project to our class. The impact we wanted to show was how the VTA can provide commuters with a more reliable and efficient form of transportation for commuters.\n \n \no Using GitHub and Slack to alleviate communication conflicts during project management\no Creating and present our project presentation through Microsoft Project\n', u'title': u'VTA Consolidation Project'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.8 ~ 2016.12', u'description': u'o Constructing a bootable Linux USB drive in a universal multiboot installer while identifying physical security features\no Simulating server management database that allocates resources initially virtualized on Microsoft servers\no Executing agile approach to assist with project development and achieve weekly milestones', u'title': u'Virtualization - Business Strategy and Telecommunications'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.8 ~ 2016.12', u'description': u'In this project, we created a functioning website that mimics a storefront.  We choose to create,test and implement a store that sold mobile accessories. The goal of the project was to utilize various coding languages including:  HTML, JavaScript, CSS, PHP. We modified the code of a template on a bootstrap application until we were able to perform the functions we wanted to successfully operate our store. We included an aesthetically pleasing main page, contacts, feedback, people and 5 products. Working in a group of two, we delegated task accordingly and completed the project in a timely manner by consistently meeting deadlines. Through multiple trials, we were able to successfully create this website to our satisfaction.\n\n', u'title': u'Online Store Front Website - Web Based Computing'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.2 ~ 2016.5', u'description': u'UniNaps was a business plan we created to introduce a solution to an escalating problem amongst students, faculty, and working professionals. Sleep deprivation can lead to fatigue and decrease in performance whether at school or at work. The purpose of UniNaps was to provide business institutions a comfortable and convenient solution that was hygienic, non-invasive, and secure. This plan was originally targeting the student body of San Jose State University with the hopes to further expand into public and private institutions such as libraries, companies, and even airports. \n\nThe opportunity was the amount of students and business professionals who are not performing to their potential due to their lack of sleep. The benefits of sleep are constantly preached yet ignored. By initially targeting San Jose State, we hope to gradually reach out to all departments on campus. Such a big institution with over 30,000 can definitely utilize these napping pods to better the morale and performance of their students and also faculty. This can serve as a healthier alternative than a cup of coffee or energy boosters.\n\nThe market share for this is huge as SJSU has numerous departments that can use this resource which include: the various buildings on campus, parking services, student health center, athletics, and student housing. \n\nOur competitive advantage is that our napping pods were designed to be cost efficient, easy to handle, package, manufacture, store and was shaped in an optimal napping position. \n\nFor this business plan, we create a design prototype, SWOT analysis, realistic startup capital, financial analysis, strategic business model, return of investment, profit projections, marketing strategies, and a detailed timeline of the overall implementation plan.\n', u'title': u'UniNaps Business Plan'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.8 ~ 2015.12', u'description': u'We were tasked to create an online library database. This project was completed with Visual Basic. The components of this project included an aesthetically pleasing design overall, fully functioning login page, sign up page, check-out and return page, and current bookings page. These were all tested to accept only relevant data and to catch any falsely implemented information like an actual library database. Some skills I learned are:\no\tAdvanced project management through the implementation of weekly project deadlines and ground rules\no\tIncorporated cadences from Agile Development Methodology including sprints and iterations during development\no\tProper execution of Microsoft Access and Visual Studios in a group of 3 members to create an electronic database\n', u'title': u'Electronic Library Database - Fundamentals of Management Information Systems'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.1 ~ 2016.5', u'description': u'o Developing databases to properly manipulate data and create appropriate entity-relationships, queries, and forms \no Execution of quality projects through proper understanding of My SQL Workbench and Oracle SQL developer  \no Eluding technical errors and quantitative business problems through the proper incorporation of data and analytics', u'title': u'Systems Analysis and Design'}]

summary: Are you frustrated with your relationships? Do you think that others ignore you or treat you in a rude, mean or disrespectful way? Do you think that others don't listen to you or care about your opinion? I can help you work things out with others so you can move forward smoothly with all your life goals. \n\nMany people suffer painful emotions when they interact with others and they think it's the way life has to be. If you've tried to make changes and failed, you might  feel helpless or hopeless. You don't have to struggle alone and we can transform your situation!\n\nYour interactions with others CAN be easygoing and stress-free! I can show you the root of your problems with others and how to heal from it, so you can feel CONFIDENT and self-assured in your dealings with others. \n\nI am an expert at identifying relationship problems and how to solve them. Most interpersonal conflicts stem from unhealthy limiting beliefs and conditionings. I will help you to identify them, then show you a simple process to quickly and effectively release unhealthy beliefs. I don't use EFT (tapping) - only a simple verbal process that clears beliefs for GOOD.\n\nIt has worked wonders for so many of my clients. They are amazed at the progress they make over several sessions on issues that have held them back for YEARS! Best of all, by working with me, you will learn to do the process yourself and make rapid progress by working through your issues at home. You can even help your friends and family this way. \n\nFor a complimentary Relationship Breakthrough Strategy Session, go to:\nhttps://relategreat.coachesconsole.com/v2/web/relationship-breakthrough--strategy-session.html\n\n\nSpeaker Presentations on the following topics:\nEffective Communication, Relationship skills, Assertiveness, Managing Anger, Stress Management and much more.\n\nSpecialties: Fast, effective Release of Unhealthy Beliefs and Freedom from the Past

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2013.4 ~ 2013.6', u'description': u'Conducted an individual three month period ethnographic (qualitative) master fieldwork research in Yogyakarta, Indonesia.\nThe research explored the way in which \u201cthe figure of the child\u201d in Indonesia and in the cultural capital Yogyakarta articulates itself and can be identified in different forms of visual culture. I also examined how this \u201cfigure\u201d can get an ascribed ideological value through the influence of state ideologies and pedagogical practices, which have an effect in the way schoolchildren see themselves and the environment of which they are a part of. The focus of the thesis was thus how children in Indonesia become \u201cagents of vision\u201d.\nThe research was conducted in four sites: an elementary school; a collective filmproject who works with children; a children\u2019s library; and the images of children in urban space and television.\nResearchmethods: literature study; participant observation; in-depth interviews; observation; and well thought of task-based activities to advance children\u2019s participation.\n', u'title': u'Individual Master (Research) Fieldwork'}]

summary: Hello! summary: I am a psychotherapist specializing in relationship counseling. I bring an understanding of the physiological and emotional connections of relationships into my practice with couples. I understand how relationships work well and what happens within and between partners when connections are broken. My style of practice is based on attachment research and builds on the natural strengths of each individual. Using an educational and skill building approach I help my clients understand their dynamic, see their issues more clearly and develop their abilities and skill to use the power they have in their relationships to feel better and deepen connections. \n

summary: Pam's expertise is in organization psychology and she understands what makes people tick - how they think and act.  Her specialty is creating change in people and workplaces with a focus on helping them stop doing what does not work.\n\nPam focuses her change in three areas:\n1.  Exit Strategy Planning (www.strategytoexit.com)\nHelping people and business prepare exit strategies and succession is exciting. This is change management at its finest when individual coaching and management training create consistency and predictability of the future . . . and improve succession\n\n2.  Performance Management (www.thepossibilities.ca)\nThrough her strategic program (Building Better Bosses) and training, management becomes accountable, better communicators and consistent leaders.  Performance and productivity improve when cohesion and collaboration replace tension from bad bosses. \n\n3. Clinical Therapist (www.pampaquet.com)\nRegistered with the Canadian Counselling Association to offer clinical therapy services to people, executive and companies.  Pam offers a unique program of therapy to staff and consulting to management.   \n\nSpecialties: Conflict resolution, stress management, communication, managing generations, leadership, business assertiveness, retirement transition, goal setting & motivation.

summary: Samuel is a software engineer with over 20 years of hands-on experience. He's helped to architect, develop, test and deliver solutions for several different niches such as education, retail, financial, telecom, energy, risk management and others. He is also an author, trainer, speaker, entrepreneur and an experienced executive. \n\nHe had the opportunity to deliver global solutions built with the most advanced technologies, platforms and architectures to date such as Java, C#, C Ansi, PHP, Ruby and RubyOnRails, GWT, Python, Node.js, Angular.js, React.js, React Native, Android, IOS, and others.\n\nSamuel had been the founder and CEO of OnCast, a company that provided software outsourcing and helped to establish a new standard for lean and agile software development, influencing the culture a large community of software companies. \n  \nIn 2015 he founded LeanIT101.com - a consulting firm with a global team that offers transformation solutions comprehending everything to really make lasting transformations. LeanIT101 services range from coaching the executives, to digging in and teaching developers on how to write clean code using TDD.\n\nSamuel created the Lean Pyramid, a software engineering model that helps to balance efforts and understand the myriad of aspects related to transform how a company delivers software. Samuel currently maintains the blog piramidelean.com.br (portuguese) and is soon starting the english version at theleanpyramid.com.\n\nSamuel is a frequent speaker at national and international conferences. He had been a co-founder and chairman of agile conferences such as Ágiles2009, Pensando Lean Forum, Agile Brazil and the Lean IT Summit Brazil. \n\nSamuel is a former member of the board of directors of the Agile Alliance where he helped to manage the multi-million dollar budget and expand the organization's operations internationally. He's helped to create the Agile Alliance Brazil and Agile Alliance New Zealand, the first arms of the organization outside USA.

summary: Matthew Goss is the Founder of StrategyDB, a trading technology service provider that delivers trading analytics and intelligence to the financial markets.\n\nMr. Goss was recently the Director of Business Development, part of the team at Confluentia Group, responsible for engaging with industry leaders, making key contacts, and building relationships with the C-Lvl decision makers at the major banks, broker-dealers, exchanges, utilities and governmental agencies. \n\nBefore joining Confluentia, Matt also worked at FlexTrade Systems, ran his own floor member firm as a member on the NYMEX & COMEX exchanges, managed money for Bankers Trust, and also ran the metals book at Goldman Sachs.\n\nAn accomplished financial industry multi-disciplined director, with noted success in custom financial consulting, business development, experience building sales pipelines, constructing corporate strategies, and building customer relationships, Mr. Goss leads with conviction.\n\nThe core of his experience before 2007 was focused on multi-asset class trading including, U.S., Asian, and Latam markets, trading analytics product development, trading strategy authorship, and multi-asset class alpha generation trading systems creation.

summary: I am a Registered Psychotherapist, Psychometrist and Mental Health Clinician, educated with a Masters degree in Clinical Psychology and an Hons. B.A. in Psychology. I am a Professional Member of the Canadian Counselling and Psychotherapy Association (CCPA) and am a Registered Psychotherapist with the College of Registered Psychotherapists of Ontario (CRPO). My areas of focus include working with individuals experiencing a variety of issues, with particular interest in trauma, PTSD, anxiety and mood disorders, self-esteem, substance abuse and addictions, attachment, relationship issues, anger management, executive coaching, stress, sleep and pain management and concurrent disorders. My therapeutic approach is personalized to the client, utilizing combined modalities including CBT, DBT, Mindfulness, and Psychodynamic approaches. I seek to provide a safe atmosphere to deeply connect and collaboratively work with clients to elicit positive changes in their lives. In addition, I have interest and experience in administering psychological assessments and writing assessment reports. \n\nI have over 10 years experience in executive-level support, providing me skills relevant to prioritizing, project management, time management, excellent communication and organizational skills, discretion, process improvement, and a high attention to detail. \n\nVisit my website at: www.mindsettoronto.com \n\nSPEAKING ENGAGEMENTS:\n\nSpeaker / Presenter  |  Coca-Cola Refreshments |  Feb, 2016\n-Facilitated workshop session on Mindfulness\n\nChair / Course Leader & Lecturer   |   Federated Press   |   Feb, 2016\n-Facilitated workshops on Mindfulness Techniques, Assertiveness, Priority Setting and Time Management Strategies\n\nChair / Course Leader & Lecturer   |   Federated Press   |   Feb, 2015\n-Facilitated workshops on Mindfulness Techniques, Priority Setting and Time Management Strategies\n

summary: My current activities entail, amongst others, enabling change agents and guiding organisations, often in healthcare, in becoming purpose driven and having a more positive impact on the world around them. \n\nI enjoy the irony of my last name being ‘Sana’, which also means ‘Health’ in Latin. As coincidence would have it, I have a background in healthcare: from having started a foundation in human centred care, running leadership programmes for healthcare professionals, and having the experience of being one of the first ‘chief compassionate officers’ in a healthcare institute. \n\nAfter having lived the entrepreneurial life for some years, I decided I wanted to have more impact with the work I was doing. It was at that moment that I decided to join the fantastic tribe at Better Future. \n\nYou can find me living in the south of Amsterdam, using my bike to get around the city and building some consistency in cross-fit, reading and writing/publishing. I try learning something new whenever I get the chance. After having finished a course in percussion last autumn, and just of late dived into the world of Yoga after a wonderful vacation in Thailand. With the endless things I would still like to learn, such as, video editing, photography and storytelling, I continue to shape my know-how in online, marketing and social media. \n\nIf you would like to read more about my experience, please scroll down below. Drop me a message and connect with me either here on Linkedin or elsewhere online: Instagram, Twitter or Facebook. \n\nThank you for reading and Take Care :)

summary: Hello! I am a Psychology Fellow at Naperville Counseling Center, a private practice in Naperville, IL, and an Adjunct Professor at Adler University in Chicago, IL. Through the center, I conduct psychological assessments and evaluations of clients as well as provide therapy services. As an adjunct, I teach a course on Adlerian Theory, which includes training doctoral students to assess and interpret a formal Lifestyle Assessment. I recently completed my doctoral degree in Clinical Psychology with an emphasis in Advanced Adlerian Psychotherapy at Adler University in Chicago, IL. I am currently awaiting licensure in the state of Illinois. My current areas of interest are in psychological assessment, private practice, clients in transition, Adlerian theory and therapy, and the role of technology within the field of psychology.

summary: I’m a proactive agile coach, with extensive knowledge of agile processes (XP, Scrum, Kanban, SAFe, Disciplined Agile Delivery) and the technical practices required to make an agile team productive and successful (TDD, BDD, Pair Programming, Mob Programming, Clean Code). I enjoy helping teams transform into effective and productive agile teams. Using a Servant Leadership style I’m able to help the team grow at the same time as ensuring the team hits all objectives that have been set. Communication is key for any team to be successful both internally to the team and externally to stakeholders. Using techniques from BDD to allow us to create a ubiquitous language for specifications we can ensure that the whole team has an understanding of what is required. A high level of openness reduces the need for conflict resolution, but when this is required I feel have the humility and assertiveness to resolve issues swiftly and effectively. \n\nI find that an agile team works best by selecting the agile practices from many different methodologies that work for them. Although this needs to be underpinned with Technical Practices for example Test Driven Development, Behaviour Driven Development, Pair Programming and Clean Code. As well as being an Agile Coach / Scrum Master / Kanban Practitioner I’m a practising software craftsman. I understand that having a clean code base and correctly structured modules will help a team keep agile and moving fast. I’m driven by the desire for successful outcomes. \n\nI’m able to facilitate many different types of meetings, from the standard agile ceremonies – Daily Stand-ups, Planning Meetings, Retrospectives to more formal business meetings for requirements gatherings and stakeholder management with regular updates on project status.\n

summary: North Oakland Anxiety Center was developed with a specific goal in mind: To empower clients who suffer from anxiety by providing a clear path to the peace and confidence in life that they deserve.\n  \nRebecca Ehle,LMSW is a clinical social worker and an anxiety specialist with over 25 years of experience.  Her down to earth and relatable style makes it easy for children, teens and adults alike to get comfortable in therapy and quickly use step by step interventions to make progress. summary: Prasann Sharma is a BABCP Accredited Cognitive Behavioural Psychotherapist and Registered Member BACP Counsellor (Reg. MBACP). Prasann has worked as a CBT Psychotherapist and Psychological Wellbeing Practitioner with the NHS, England between 2009 and 2017. Prasann has also practised as an Associate Counsellor with SOAS, University of London 2008-09. Prasann holds a Masters degree in Counselling and Psychotherapy from University of East London and a Post Graduate Diploma in CBT from University of Surrey. Prasann also holds a PG Diploma in Counselling and Psychotherapy, London and PG Certificate in Psychological Wellbeing Practice, Salomons. Prasann is trained and experienced in delivering evidence based CBT interventions for a wide range of mental health difficulties like stress, anxiety and depression. Alongside traditional CBT, Prasann is also a qualified and experienced counsellor. His counselling training and approach is based on 'Integrative Model', which simply means that he employs a variety of therapeutic approaches according to the client presentation. Prasann has worked with various client groups, including young people, working age adults, older people, people with disabilities, long term health conditions, various ethnic and religious backgrounds and LGBTQI community. Currently working as a High Intensity Cognitive Behavioural Psychotherapist, offering psychological therapy and assessment appointments to individuals experiencing moderate to severe symptoms of depression and anxiety. Prasann practices in accordance with the codes of ethics of professional bodies like BABCP and BACP. Prasann is passionate about helping clients reach a better understanding of their situation and also to help them gain new skills and reach their full potential. Areas of specialisation include depression, low self esteem, generalised anxiety, PTSD, OCD, panic disorder, bereavement, anger management, relationship difficulties, self harm and substance abuse.\n

summary: On board sailing ship Ciganka we offer Youth Groups a positive platform to “stretch” themselves in new directions which will build self confidence, assertiveness, determination, an attitude of always doing your best, and will give them with a broader view of life.  On top of all that we have an absolute blast!  \n\nYou will learn all the aspects of running and sailing this traditionally rigged tall ship.  This is a participating charter when you, a crew member, will work together with your shipmates as a team.\n\nYou will sail the amazing Abaco Islands in the beautiful Bahamas.  This northern chain of Bahamian islands offers some of the best sailing in the world! The lay of the islands offers protection from the ocean's waves and swells allowing calm sailing in a big bay.  Every day we will sail to explore different islands, beaches, and reefs. And every night we will anchor behind an island enjoying our own piece of paradise.\n\nAre you sure you want a high adventure?  Because this is what you will get on board Ciganka!  That is why 92% of our charter groups come back to sail with us again!  Experience a true sailing adventure on the only tall ship in the Abacos, Bahamas!

summary: Ambitious professional with expertise in communication, human relations, industrial/org. psychology, leadership development & coaching.\nLeadership training, using motivational psychology, coaching, & behavioral assessments to improve productivity, performance & profit.\n \nWith over 20 years experience helping leaders develop emotional intelligence, I bridge the gap between where they are now & where they want to be.  I help newly promoted/challenged leaders who may know their trade but must now achieve results through others via leadership skills.  \n\nAccelerated learning methods allow participants to learn faster, remember more, & have more fun. Unique self-assessments address leadership from the inside out. Role-play practice ensures that participants do what they know (not just know what to do). As your coach, I ask powerful yet difficult questions, challenging you to take action in spite of self-defeating beliefs, doubts & fears. As college faculty, I researched, developed & taught several different courses. I use this expertise to make you a better leader & improve your team's performance.\n\nWe start with a 360 assessment, DISC, EQ & StrengthsFinder then negotiate an individualized action plan based on assessment results to encourage accountability. I say it like it is, observe you in your setting & help you be your best. As a result, you see how you affect others & how they see you. Most people won't tell you this stuff. But, I show you what holds you back & what can propel you forward.\n\nSpecialties: -Certified DISC Behavioral Analyst\n-Conducting 360s, DISC, EQ & other assessments\n-Helping newly promoted leaders develop leadership skills, manage time/stress & achieve work-life balance\n-Helping busy, smart but scattered, driven yet distracted leaders/professionals increase focus, goal attainment, organization, productivity, & performance\n-Showing de-railed, abrasive, command-and-control leaders how to motivate employees more positively and collaboratively

summary: Marianne Perez de Fransius helps people see the value of and access peace in their daily lives so that we can all live in a better world. She does this by teaching middle school kids peace and conflict transformation skills through video games; and helping parents travel the world with their babies.\n\nMarianne makes peace tangible as a peaceworker and educator, developing curricula and training for students and adults/professionals. Specializing in conflict transformation and peace media, she creates peace media in which conflict transformation, community empowerment and personal development are seen as sexy, entertaining, empowering, engaging and profitable. Through Sipala Labs, she is working on a Peace Superheroes digital game to teach conflict resolution and transformation skills to kids in a fun and engaging way. \n\nIn her other venture, Bébé Voyage, Marianne and her partner, Juliet Bazire d'Arguesse, have identified a highly under-served market: parents traveling with babies. Their membership group, Club Bébé Voyage, has grown to 5000 members by word-of-mouth. In their first year, Marianne and Juliet have developed an acclaimed website, established a strong social media presence, appeared in the Wall Street Journal, the New York Post, and Travel Weekly, amongst other publications, helped pass a law to improve airport screening of infant feeding equipment and established strong relationships with key players in the travel industry. \n\n\nAVAILABLE FOR:\n- Training in a variety of professional development areas\n- Courses in Peace Media and Peace Journalism\n- Workshops for peace studies students, activists, journalists and other media professionals\n- Facilitating dialogues around difficult topics\n\nSpecialties: Experiential workshops, dialogue facilitation, media development\n\nMost recent peer-reviewed journal article:\nPeace Journalism Case Study: US Media Coverage of the Iraq War\nhttp://jou.sagepub.com/content/early/2013/01/15/1464884912470313.abstract

summary: Call today 904-748-9106 or www.ThomasTherapyServices.com\n\nThere are times in life that may require intervention and support from a professional. Trauma, bereavement, relationships, work stress and interpersonal struggles all influence function and productivity. Taking the opportunity to work through life’s challenges has great reward for successful quality of life.\n\nAmie Thomas, MSW, LCSW is a Licensed Clinical Social Worker (LCSW) in the state of Florida. She has been a professional Social Worker for the past 18+ years in various settings both private and not for profit. Ms. Thomas has a Bachelor’s degree in Social Work (BSW) from Auburn University and a Master’s degree in Social Work (MSW) from Alabama Agricultural & Mechanical University.\n\nMs. Thomas provides psychotherapy services designed to address needs that complicate daily coping. Services are provided using empowerment and cognitive theories. Service focus is directed to individuals, groups, women’s issues, adolescents (12 and up), and adults.\n\n“I am very honored and blessed to provide services in this capacity. Coping and validating the taxing ordeals of daily living creates endurance and maturity for forward purpose and enhancement of our lives and others.”\n\nSpecialties: Adult, adolescent and youth issues, depression and anxiety, Women's Issues, Groups: Parenting groups, Life Skills, Self Assessment, Grief issues (for individuals and groups).

summary: For the last 20 years I have worked as a systemic psychotherapist, life coach, dramatherapist and educator (The Priory Group, Amplify Presentations Ltd, BUPA, AXA/PPP, Middlesex University).  In recent years I have combined my creative and therapeutic experience to provide a unique approach to executive business coaching. (ThinkShield)\n \nI am an international speaker and workshop leader with wide teaching experience. (Singapore, Kuwait, London) as well as being a published author of a book on addiction. \n\nI am passionate about helping clients make new stories to promote creativity and overcome blocks to change. My coaching is interactive, lively, engaging and uses the skills of systemic therapy and drama. I enable clients to create new stories based on their strengths. This 'Appreciative' Enquiry' approach is a very positive way of generating fresh solutions and getting unstuck from old stories. In my workshops I use a three stage model (M.C.T) This provides training in mindfulness and creativity leading to actionable transformation. \n\nAndre Radmall Consulting offers a range of workshops, from a one hour 'creativity booster'  to three hour M.C.T workshops. From two-day creative problem solving intensives to six months programs.\n\nCurrent Partnerships include story-telling and mindfulness workshops with Amplify Presentations Limited (Microsoft Impact Coaching)\n\nMy workshops contain dynamic, creative and energising material that gives quick and lasting results. I use a range of techniques including mindfulness, improvisation, film clips, mind-mapping, listening skills, assertiveness work and appreciative enquiry.\n\nwww.andreradmall.co.uk

summary: I am a licensed clinical psychologist in private practice in the greater Chicagoland area. I am currently interested in opportunities for short-term writing projects, columns, or media consultations on mental health topics of interest. \n\nI obtained both my MA (2006) and my Psy.D. (2010) in clinical psychology from the Chicago School of Professional Psychology. I obtained my BS Magna Cum Laude with Honors in Psychology from Barry University in 2003. \n\nI am experienced in evaluating, treating, and designing school and home based interventions with specialized populations, including: ADHD evaluations and treatment planning; clients with major affective disorders, anxiety, PTSD & traumatic syndromes, and psychotic disorders; clients struggling with addiction, traumatic loss and bereavement; at-risk adolescents and family conflict; families with a loved one with Autism/Aspergers disorder; ethnically diverse and cross-cultural families; adjustment disorders, unemployment, legal and/or life stressors. I also specialize in working with divorced and blended families, as well as children and families who are exploring issues related to cultural concerns, acculturation, and identity development.\n\nI maintain a strengths-based, holistic, and collaborative approach to psychotherapy informed by relational, family systems, and trauma recovery theories with specialized expertise in group therapy, DBT and Tf-CBT, family planning and parenting training, complex trauma recovery, gender identity development and trans and LGBT community support. \n\nI have a deep commitment to community outreach, family advocacy, and prevention services, and multicultural competence.

summary: Sharon is a well respected coach with  extensive experience of personal and professional coaching across sectors. She has a wide range of expertise and an understanding of organisational and personal change. \nSharon specialises in coaching current and aspiring leaders to be highly effective, resilient and maintain their well being.  Her strength is in building authentic relationships and working with integrity across organisations using  a bespoke blend of coaching, training and facilitation to help people and organisations fulfil their potential. \n\nShe is pursuing opportunities to work with aspiring  and current leaders in forward thinking organisations.\n\nCurrent In-house Training Opportunities:\nLeadership Styles and Skills\nPeople Management Skills\nManaging Challenging Conversations\nEffective Team Building and Working\nCreating and Implementing a Shared Vision\nDeveloping a Growth Mindset\nProfessional Effectiveness\nWorkload Management and Work Life Balance\nDeveloping Coaching Skills  \n\n\n Areas of Specialisation: \nLeadership, education, emotional intelligence, delegation skill, motivation self and others, communication skills, achieving success, positive psychology, teams, change management, assertiveness, prioritising, problem solving, decision making, reflective practitioner, strategic thinking, confidence building, managing transitions, goal setting, working strategically, creativity, managing uncertainty, challenging behaviour, learning styles, attachment theory, stress management, cognitive behaviour therapy, solution focussed therapy, transactional analysis, profiling, person centred practice, NLP.

summary: Overworked? Overwhelmed? Afraid to Speak Up? Unsure How to Lead a Team? \n\nAs an executive leader, project management consultant, coach, motivational speaker, author, wife, and mom, I know all too well how life and your career can get the best of you. Don’t let it put you down. Be a Woman Warrior, unleash the power within you, and learn to be a leader in your life. Prepare for the battles ahead and come out victorious on your terms.\n\nI specialize in helping busy professional women to:\n• Find career-life balance \n• Achieve career and personal success – yes this is possible!\n• Reduce stress\n• Tap into and build your energy level \n• Learn key leadership skills that can be applied at work and at home\n• Support your life transitions (e.g. career, new family additions, job loss, divorce, empty nest, etc.)\n\nI struggled with these issues over my 25 year corporate career. Now I combine my executive leadership and project management experience with a keen ability to hone into your challenges and help you to create new possibilities. \n\nI also provide business services for companies which include:\n• Professional Development Seminars and Workshops\n• High Performance and Team Engagement Activities & Workshops\n• Program & Project Management \n• Women’s Leadership & Diversity Training \n• Executive Leadership Training & Coaching \n• Customer Service Excellence & Professionalism Training\n• Energetic Sales Engagement Model\n• Conflict & Negotiation Skills Training\n• Motivational Speaking on Leadership Topics for Your Internal Employee Engagement Groups\n• Business Coaching & Team Engagement for Medical Practice Owners & Entrepreneurs \n\nIt’s time to take charge of your life and not let it take charge of you! I encourage you to take me up on a complimentary coaching session and be amazed at how coaching can change your life.

summary: Grab The Wheel: Helping Young Children Manage Explosive Anger, a new book for kids, is a visual and highly interactive curriculum, designed to help children improve emotional coping and social skills.  It is geared to be accessible to children with Autism, and to be beneficial to the early emotional development of any child.\n\nI am a constantly learning and evolving social worker, therapist, and individual.  I am a life-long learner and explorer, seeking knowledge and value in learning from a wide range of individuals and cultures.  \n\nI aim to combine my experiences working with a diverse array of Children, Adolescents, and Adults with mental illness and developmental disabilities into a knowledgeable and humble base that will allow me to be helpful to anyone who I meet.  As a behavioral therapist, I strive to create imaginative, effective, and practical interventions to serve the needs of individuals and their families.  As an Certified Anger Management Facilitator (CAMF) and member of Anderson & Anderson, I strive to help integrate Anger Management and Emotional Intelligence skill building into useful solutions for individuals in any industry.  As a social worker, I am committed to improving access to quality services for everyone.

summary: contact Julie info@newlooknewlifeconsulting.com 250-658-6390. Julie is not perfect.  She knows it.  And she has finally come to realize that she doesn't have to be.  It has been a long road for Julie to make peace with imperfection.  Growing up, she found that projecting an image of perfection was a flawed yet familiar safeguard against her troubled family life.  If she seemed perfect on the outside, no one would know the demons she faced.  No one would see her anguish, her fear, her anger.  Julie  channeled her need to be perfect into helping and healing others as she entered adulthood.  Witnessing a high school friend recover from severe burns inspired Julie to take up nursing.  She discovered she had deep compassion for helping patients through their healing process. She dedicated many years of nursing to trauma and burn patients and reconstruction. This is where she began to understand the power of being able to help others see themselves as beautiful.  Julie's natural progression in her nursing led her into plastic cosmetic surgery.  In providing support to women before and after, she encouraged women to look honestly at themselves, to begin to see the beauty within. Julie now dedicates her life to encouraging the power of transformation. She embraces her role as a catalyst for change, in her own life and in the lives of others.

summary: I'm a former psychotherapist and relationship coach who helps women transform their relationship with themselves, the Universe, and everything in between and couples transform their relationship with one another into healthy, vibrant, thriving love. \n\nAll of my work encompasses a spiritual edge, which is why I also run a spiritual podcast called Wild & Holy Radio.  \n\nIt's my personal mission to help others find their truth, live their truth, and create lives that honor their soul.  I do this through my podcast, 1-1 coaching with women and couples, and leading small intimate retreats for women called Wild & Holy Weekend.  \n\nThe next Wild & Holy Weekend is being offered September 22-24, 2017 in Austin, TX.  To find out more, you can visit wildandholyweekend.com and to listen to my podcast, you can find me on iTunes at bit.ly/WildandHolyRadio.

summary: Martine Cantrel\n\nMartine has 28-year experience as a project manager, consultant and business owner, and 18 years as a Learning Tree instructor.  She holds a degree in International Business from a French university and has the PMP and PMI-ACP certifications.\n\nAs part of an international engineering team, she evaluated project feasibility and managed the implementation of an import/export logistic platform for Alcatel and managed projects for the construction of waste-to-energy conversion plants for Babcock/CNIM. She has also worked pro bono for humanitarian organizations managing projects targeted at educating street children. \n\nUpon moving to the United States 18 years ago, she founded an IT consulting company, which is currently managing projects using the Agile project management techniques for projects ranging from Web applications, using HTML5 and .Net, to iPhone apps. It is through her consulting company that she started to teach for Learning Tree International. \n\nBecause of the variety of projects, she has managed, her international exposure and the ability to speak four languages, she brings a colorful palette of extraordinary examples to her courses, to illustrate project management concepts and to help learners grasp and retrain the related theories.\n\nShe likes to emphasize that Learning Tree is “Education that you Can Trust”. A Learning Tree course is always provided with a 100% customer satisfaction guarantee. In other words, organizations get value for their training investment.\n

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2014.6 ~ 2015.6', u'description': u'Desde el a\xf1o 1997 la Refiner\xeda Esmeraldas RE forma parte del Sistema Nacional Interconectado, parte del requerimiento energ\xe9tico necesario para su funcionamiento es suministrado a trav\xe9s del Sistema Nacional Interconectado en forma permanente, el pago que se realiza mensualmente impacta directamente en los costos de producci\xf3n del barril de petr\xf3leo procesado, lo cual ocasiona que durante todo ese tiempo exista egresos econ\xf3micos por su facturaci\xf3n mensual a pesar de contar con capacidad de generaci\xf3n suficiente como para abastecer el consumo interno y ofrecer al Mercado El\xe9ctrico Mayorista.\n\nConsiderando lo mencionado, a trav\xe9s de este trabajo se analiza el marco legal y el entorno del sector el\xe9ctrico ecuatoriano referente a la comercializaci\xf3n de energ\xeda el\xe9ctrica adem\xe1s de la posibilidad de transaccionar los excedentes de energ\xeda el\xe9ctrica de la RE.\n\nSe realiza una estimaci\xf3n del volumen de la energ\xeda excedente que podr\xeda comercializarse en el Mercado El\xe9ctrico Mayorista y el impacto econ\xf3mico beneficioso para la Refiner\xeda Esmeraldas considerando el precio de la unidad de energ\xeda kWh vigente determinado por el Consejo Nacional de Electricidad CONELEC y el Centro Nacional de Control de Energ\xeda CENACE, organismos encargado de regular y administrar t\xe9cnicamente el sector el\xe9ctrico.\n\nSe presenta la metodolog\xeda usada para establecer un plan estrat\xe9gico apropiado para la naturaleza de la empresa, que permitir\xe1 orientar a las autoridades a tomar las mejores decisiones. Se presenta un an\xe1lisis de las Fortalezas, Oportunidades, Debilidades, Amenazas, FODA con que cuenta la  empresa, as\xed como la matriz de evaluaci\xf3n de factores externos e internos.', u'title': u'Plan estrat\xe9gico de la Refiner\xeda Esmeraldas para convertirlo de gran consumidor en auto productor de energ\xeda el\xe9ctrica'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.10 ~ 2014.10', u'description': u'Tras la crisis econ\xf3mica mundial o gran recesi\xf3n mundial a partir del a\xf1o 2008, los costos \nde las materias primas se incrementaron, particularmente la del precio del petr\xf3leo, \ncausando verdaderos da\xf1os econ\xf3micos y amenazando a las econom\xedas de los pa\xedses en \ndesarrollo.', u'title': u'MODELO DE CONTROL DE COSTOS DE PERFORACI\xd3N DE POZOS PARA LOS CAMPOS CUYABENO-VHR DE LA PETROAMAZONAS EP'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.6 ~ 2015.6', u'description': u'El crecimiento econ\xf3mico es la condici\xf3n necesaria aunque no suficiente para el desarrollo humano y sostenible, este incremento es posible aumentando las oportunidades de empleo y generando recursos para el Estado v\xeda tributaci\xf3n, aunque la experiencia latinoamericana muestra que todo depende de la \u201ccalidad\u201d del crecimiento econ\xf3mico para concretar estas posibilidades, por ello, es necesario vincular el desempe\xf1o econ\xf3mico con una verdadera transformaci\xf3n productiva.\n \nLa estructura productiva del Ecuador adolece de grandes limitaciones estructurales y de  funcionamiento, que se expresa entre otros elementos por una exagerada dependencia de la explotaci\xf3n de un bien no renovable como es el petr\xf3leo, ello incide en la desarticulaci\xf3n entre los diferentes sectores, baja productividad, presencia de estructuras monop\xf3licas, reducida diversificaci\xf3n de las exportaciones de bienes y servicios.\n\nEcuador es uno de los pa\xedses latinoamericanos con mayor desigualdad distributiva, una peque\xf1a proporci\xf3n de la poblaci\xf3n se concentra buena parte del ingreso nacional, mientras la gran mayor\xeda apenas accede a una m\xednima parte de este ingreso. Lo rescatable, luego de la dolarizaci\xf3n, es la relativa estabilidad monetaria, que se debe a la utilizaci\xf3n de una moneda que no es propia del pa\xeds. \n \nEntre los principales problemas que afronta el pa\xeds, es la inestabilidad del desarrollo econ\xf3mico, social y pol\xedtico, los modelos econ\xf3micos que han implementado sea con pol\xedticas neoliberales, austeras, devaluatorias, de excesivo endeudamiento interno y externo, dispersi\xf3n del gasto sin calidad, disminuci\xf3n y posteriormente aumento del aparato estatal en toda su dimensi\xf3n, limitada inversi\xf3n extranjera, inestabilidad jur\xeddica y laboral, son factores que no permiten el progreso sostenido y sistem\xe1tico del pa\xeds.\n', u'title': u'Desarrollo de un plan de negocios y an\xe1lisis de inversi\xf3n para una cooperativa de ahorro y cr\xe9dito'}]

summary: I'm very passionate in everything that I get into. I completed M.Sc. studies in industrial engineering and management, which was followed by a need to learn more by studying information technology. At the University of Oulu my scope shifted to working with start-ups in early stage development, namely the innovativeness and lean approaches that impact the business.\n\nMy background is diverse and international. I am internationally experienced, having worked, studied and lived 10 years in Florence, Italy. Traveling is part of my everyday life and seeing more than 50 countries taught me many things about international business. \n\nMy work experience reaches from business operations management and project coordination to customer service and sales. I am curious and driven to learn, and enthusiastic about technology and modern IT-solutions and life-improving implementations.\n\nColleagues know me as a highly creative worker who can always be trusted to come up with a new approach. But I know that the client’s business comes first, and I never try to impose my ideas on others. Instead, I spend a lot of time understanding the business and the audience before suggesting ideas. I can (and often do) work well alone, but I’m at my best collaborating with others.\n\nOverall, my background enables a holistic and systemic view on problem solving, and I am always looking to work in challenging environments with people from different cultures.

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2014.6 ~ 2014.6', u'description': u'', u'title': u'The Lamb'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2008.1 ~ 2008.1', u'description': u'Bogo Shock Nasty\u2014an aging ex-con who finds himself burnt-out and working at a local liquor store, receives an unexpected visit from an old friend who confronts him about his change in occupation. Triggering Bogo's inner gangster self to resurface, Bogo finds himself reconnecting with his notorious ex-drug dealer Stubs . With very little money to front his new prospects, Bogo is forced to take a huge risk in order to regain the respect he once had from his peers. His plan\u2014to rob Syph and double-up on his money but he quickly realizes he is not the sharp gangster he used to be and finds himself on the other side of the gun. With his back against the wall, Bogo is forced to make a life-changing decision in order to payback the notorious Stubs and reclaim his own agency.\n\nDirector Statement\nThis movie deals directly with the mundane influence that mainstream hip hop culture has on my generation, the so-called Generation Y. So many kids grow up believing that if you sell drugs and rap you can be the next 2Pac. Unfortunately this is not reality and a lot of people I\u2019ve grown up with discover this after either serving time in prison or by working at Rite Aid for ten years straight, suddenly realizing they have been mislead by the glamour-trip of mainstream hip hop. By making this film, I wanted to touch on aspects of life that resonate deeply with me and my peers--ideals of success and struggles with disillusionment. Filmmaking is a very personal expression for me and I felt that this particular story is one that I have heard a million times--the kid who was fronted the drugs, ultimately unable to pay... so he paid with his life.', u'title': u'Bogo Shock Nasty'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2006.9 ~ 2006.9', u'description': u'A naive man haunted by mental illness, bumps into love for the first time. His dreams attack him with surreal vivid scenes of torture. She is his medicine, everything is ok wen she's around. summary: I am grateful to be included amongst so many other great like-minded individuals honored in the Phi Kappa Phi society. As an Adjunct Faculty member at Southern Oregon University I've been able to give back to the academic community by teaching in both the School of Business and Computer Science Departments. I've been fortunate to lecture and conduct labs professing my knowledge of IT/IS Management topics like MIS, Policy, and Project Management to applied technical skills required by Network Administration, Dynamic Web Design and Database Management. When I am not teaching, I serve the business community as a Consultant in first seeking to understand and later to be understood. I have enjoyed the many diverse business challenges of varying clients both large and small requiring creative IT solutions and demanding best practices of project management. Keeping abreast of the latest developments in technology keeps my interest and brain young especially in the field of Information Security and the even more demanding domain of Human Resource management.  I continue to leverage the competitive advantage illuminated by my Master's Thesis. Researching and applying the Enneagram of Personality to improve executive communication in the workplace continues to allow me the insight to understand various personality types and their motivations behind business behavior. This secret tool of business has allowed me to construct correct syntax as I interface with various human operating systems. Thus, I am grateful to Southern Oregon University's School of Business Faculty and Dr. Jennifer Joss.

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2015.11 ~ now', u'description': u'Give the things you do not need anymore away to people in your local area. Get the things you might need for free from locals.\n\nWhether you\u2019re a household or business, adding items to Givebox is easy. Simply snap a photo, add a brief description and provide pick-up details. A lovely neighbour will be delighted to take it off your hands.\n\nBrowse free items available near you, request anything that takes your fancy and message to arrange a pick-up. It\u2019s as easy as that.\n\nOur mission is to build a worldwide sharing movement that reduces waste, saves precious resources & eases the burden on our landfills while enabling our members to benefit from the strength of a larger community.\n\nTech:\n- Backend - Node JS, Socket.io & MongoDB\n- Hybrid mobile app - Ionic (Cordova, TypeScript, Angular 2 & RXJS)\n\nDownload it from Play Store: http://goo.gl/obRTbQ\nand the Apple today: https://appsto.re/ie/Ru65ib.i\n\n\uD83C\uDF89', u'title': u'Givebox - Give old things away locally (available on Android and iOS)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.3 ~ 2014.6', u'description': u'Startup Weekend is a global grassroots movement of active and empowered entrepreneurs who are learning the basics of founding startups and launching successful ventures. It is the largest community of passionate entrepreneurs with over 1800 past events in 120 countries around the world in 2014. \n\nIn June 2014 we organised the 4th Dublin Startup Weekend in Google HQ, Europe\u2019s largest Start-up Weekend so far. 135 attendees came in the door with an idea, with passion to make a difference, and most of them not knowing another person on the day. After 61 one-minute pitches on Friday evening, 21 ideas were pitched in front of 300 people in the Google Foundry on Sunday.\n\nhttp://facebook.com/SWDub\nhttp://twiiter.com/SWDub', u'title': u'Dublin Startup Weekend Summer 2014'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.11 ~ 2014.11', u'description': u'Startup Weekend is a global grassroots movement of active and empowered entrepreneurs who are learning the basics of founding startups and launching successful ventures. It is the largest community of passionate entrepreneurs with over 1800 past events in 120 countries around the world in 2014. \n\nIn November 2014 we're organising the 5th Dublin Startup Weekend, hosted in Google HQ.\n\nBlog posts about the event:\nhttp://www.up.co/communities/ireland/dublin/blog\n\nPress:\nhttp://www.businesspost.ie/#!story/Small+Business/Small+Business/Gift.me+is+overall+winner+of+Dublin's+Startup+Weekend/id/87198161-2385-4731-8e6a-93fc61150898\n\nhttp://facebook.com/SWDub\nhttp://twiiter.com/SWDub', u'title': u'Dublin Startup Weekend Winter 2014'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.6 ~ 2014.5', u'description': u'', u'title': u'Soundtravel'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.4 ~ 2013.7', u'description': u'Crate.ly facilitates easy listening of numerous audio tracks.\n\nWe discover great new music throughout the day, and sometimes, we don\u2019t have time to organize them right when we find them.\n\nCrate.ly allows you to easily save them for whenever you do have time, so you don\u2019t forget that great song or podcast.', u'title': u'Crate.ly (formerly ListenToItLater)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.5 ~ 2015.5', u'description': u'BlueTape is a connected bluetooth tape measure which connects to an app, showing the user what clothes fit them. Our pitch earned us first place, a cash prize to continue the prototyping, an office in the DCU Innovation Campus and a design workshop with Each and Other.\n\nhttp://www.independent.ie/business/technology/the-clever-tape-aimed-at-getting-the-measure-of-online-disappointments-31253402.html', u'title': u'BlueTape - Winning Project, PCH Hardware Hackathon'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.7 ~ 2013.1', u'description': u'This is a developers team which is aiming to develop social games with real location integration.\n\nNowadays, the team is looking for developers to improve the prototype of the first game.', u'title': u'The Top Hat'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.4 ~ 2015.6', u'description': u'Startup Next is an intensive five-week program that gives your team the tools and mentorship needed to navigate the early stages of building a startup.\n\nStartups accepted into the program will attend a 3-hour session once a week for five weeks. projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2012.4 ~ 2012.4', u'description': u'Jon, Walt and I worked closely with Michael and others at THS to redesign and better automated the company website and intranet. Walt produced new brand assets for both digital and print, while Jon and I developed a the site on Expression Engine. The website integrated with custom Filemaker Database systems to streamline document gathering while also remaining PCI compliant.', u'title': u'Tschetter Hamrick Sulzer'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2010.2 ~ 2012.12', u'description': u'I met Kevin and Danny of Active Junky in spring of 2010 when they were raising their seed funding and planning the next MVP launch of their website. I consulted them through the technology, development hiring, and implementation process in their initial launch, and then again in the summer of 2012. I developed their Gear Guide, architected their cloud hosting on AWS, and helped them document their platform for their future endeavors and phases in hiring developers and implementing new features.', u'title': u'Active Junky'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.11 ~ 2014.11', u'description': u'NationSearch performs background searches on individuals and businesses. Their operation was mostly manual and was hard for them to manage. We built a custom Go application to automate data collection, and then further secure and encrypt said data.', u'title': u'NationSearch Staffing Solutions'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.8 ~ 2015.8', u'description': u'As one of the most prestigious agencies in New York, getting a call from Big Spaceship is an honor. When they came to us looking for a development partner, we were excited before even knowing the work details. What unfolded was a project to build a custom application for one of the biggest tech giants, Samsung Mobile. Over the course of a few (very busy) weeks, we worked closely with YouTube engineers and Big Spaceship creatives, to quickly build and host an application that displayed a live video feed and content stream for the Samsung Unpacked event.', u'title': u'Samsung Unpacked'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.6 ~ now', u'description': u'I love to give back to the tech community. Open source has had such an amazing impact in my life, so it only made sense to combine my passions for both product and education to help build the Unicorn.TV website and classroom. Our site features tutorials, screencasts, an open community and workshops around Go, Swift, Ruby and Javascript. I focus on product management and content creation for the platform.', u'title': u'Unicorn.TV'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.9 ~ 2012.9', u'description': u'As Walt and I became acquainted with the processes and people at IREA, we immediately recognized  the need for technology to replace manual process. We consulted with many departments within the company to ascertain as many pain points possible, and immediately began building a website and infrastructure that would alleviate said issues. Leveraging Expression Engine and PHP, we built a platform that is currently supporting many processes and information collection between business and consumer. I focused on leading the dev team in product management and architecture.', u'title': u'Intermountain Rural Electric Association'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2010 ~ 2012', u'description': u'We created a custom Real Estate search platform using Kohana and MongoDB. The site stored millions of records and images imported from multiple idx providers, presenting some major challenges in normalizing data. We also created a custom back-office leveraging our own custom ACL system and a skeuomorphic design. I primarily focused on the project management, architecture and light development.', u'title': u'Qwizzle'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011 ~ 2012', u'description': u'Walt and I worked on a rebrand of the Tech Cocktail website and design assets. Walt did a stellar job creating their new logo, which has been produced on different mediums and handed to countless individuals all over the world. My role was focused on implementing the technology: servers, custom wordpress theme, SEO improvements and content creation.', u'title': u'Tech Cocktail'}]

summary: Hello, I'm Thomas Benning, an enabler of sales excellence at MongoDB. I find success in the success of others and take pride in helping our sellers understand our products in ways they never thought possible. Through experience in sales and a passion for personal growth, I am driven to help both our clients and sales team achieve their pre-defined successful outcomes.  \n\nI am currently focused on enabling our sales team here at MongoDB to achieve the highest success possible through 3 key areas:\n\n#1 Designing - Courses are best constructed with seller input so that the training courses we design are built by sales representatives for sales representatives. \n#2 Tooling - While courses can go a long way in enabling sales representative to achieve success, it is the design of new and innovative tools that help save them time and allow them to focus more deeply on their customer. \n#3 Delivering - Building tools and courses is great, but engaging delivery of these tools and courses is important for seller buy-in and retention. \n\nOur sales teams continue to function with unprecedented success to the extent that our CEO boasts that our team could trade technology with a competitor and still build a larger customer base.

summary: Vijay Vijayasankar is the GM for Cognitive, IOT, Analytics and Watson Health services for IBM GBS in North America , serving clients in all industries across US and Canada .\n\nPrior to this role, Vijay was Vice President and Partner at IBM Global Business Services , and was responsible for the Digital Transformation Services for clients in Media, Entertainment, Energy, Utilities, and Telecommunications. \n\nBefore joining IBM, Vijay ran the global channels and global services businesses at MongoDB, the leading NoSQL database company . \n\nPrior to joining MongoDB, Vijay Vijayasankar was a Global Vice President at SAP Labs, driving the engineering of Big Data applications , and worked with customers and partners to remove bottlenecks on adoption . \n\nPrior to joining SAP, Vijay was the Head of SAP Forward Engineering at IBM GBS. \nVijay has more than 14 years experience in SAP consulting for a variety of clients in North America, Europe and Asia. Vijay is IBM certified at the highest level for Technology Consulting - at Thought Leader level (PDF 6).\n\nVijay is equally proficient as a builder and as a seller , having successfully worked in and led sales and delivery in the past . \n\nVijay can be found on twitter as @vijayasankarv and his musings on all things big and small can be found at his blog \nhttp://andvijaysays.com

summary: I am an accomplished technical leader with proven track record of success, Microsoft and MongoDB certified DB professional with over 10 years of IT experience both on-premise and cloud. Hands on experience in managing large database projects including large data migration, complex process design, planning, testing and deployment, long term capacity planning.\n\nI have wide range of experience in technology stack related to database.  Few of those include:\n•\tPractical knowledge on performance tuning.\n•\tAlwaysOn Availability Groups.\n•\tTransactional replication.\n•\tDisaster recovery using different solutions.\n•\tLog shipping.\n•\tCustomized monitoring 190+ SQL engines.\n•\tSQL migration/upgrade between different versions. \n•\tCreating operational dashboard using SSRS.\n•\tMulti node SQL cluster with SAN replication to DR data center. \n•\tDesign and Implemented an enterprise grade MongoDB envirnonment with sharding, replica set using multiple data center using WiredTiger storage engine and new Ops Manager. \n•\tExperience in MongoDB (3.x) design, administration and performance tuning.\n\n\nMy recent accomplishments include:\n•      Moving selected database files to XIO and FusionIO card and reducing PAGEIOLATCH_XX wait on those files by 75%.\t\n•      Reduce off hour alert by 50%, by finding root cause and implementing permanent solution. \n•\tSaving 30% of storage footprint enterprise wide by implementing better backup solutions.  \n•\tReducing  maintenance runtime by 50% using features built into SQL Engine.\n•\tAutomated offloading DBCC CHECKDB for databases over 10TB.\n\nSpecialties: Microsoft SQL Server, Microsoft Azure implementation, MongoDB, AlwaysOn Availability Groups, Performance tuning, Capacity Planning, SSIS, SSRS, SQL Server Analysis Services, Windows 2012R2, SAN Replication, Linux.

summary: I am an accomplished technology evangelist with business sense and a passion for building highly scalable cloud based web applications backed by polyglot database architectures. I'm well versed in the whole AWS technology stack as well as, NoSQL (MongoDB since version 1.6), BigData systems like Snowflake (high performance, build for the cloud big data store), Hadoop (Cloudera), columnar data systems (Vertica, Redshift,Infobright),  as well as  traditional database technologies like MS SQLServer, Oracle, and MySql. My preferred development methodology is Dual Track Scrum by SVPG, my favorite architecture are scalability Cubes by AKF. \nMost recently I've lead the implementation of Snowflake at Snagajob and I'm currently a member of the Snowflake customer council. Snowflake enabled Snagajobs talent to focus on building applications rather than maintaining infrastructure.  Before that I've lead a team of 5 highly experienced engineers on a full lifecycle 100% AWS implementation project. The goal was to migrate the infrastructure (~ 500 VMs) from an in-house VM based platform into 100% AWS. This included replacement of bare metal load balancers and security systems with ELBs and common WAF technologies, PaaS solutions like ES (replacing Splunk), application scaling via ASG, RDS for relational repository databases, and of course migrating 25 TB of data in Vertica & Hadoop (Cloudera),  as well as multiple mongodb clusters ontop of 60 data nodes. \nI've a proven success record in multiple applications domains from shop floor automation for multi-billion dollar companies to building horizontally scalable data management (OLTP) and BigData (Analytics) platforms for web based startups. I've managed international project teams in multiple geographical locations, as well as held director level positions. Last but not least I've successfully managed multi-million dollar projects with exceptional accuracy on cost, timelines, and quality.\n

summary: For the past 17 years I've been heavily immersed in the healthcare, automotive, and general IT verticals, providing innovative technology solutions and leading technology teams. I'm incredibly passionate about what I do and attempt to inject my enthusiasm and love for technology in all those around me.\n\nI started my career in 2000 and spent 4 years building enterprise-level, database-driven Web applications. I worked for two different companies during this timeframe which included work on several high profile projects in the e-Learning space with one spanning the efforts of the Chinese Ministry of Education and the United States Department of Education.\n\nIn 2004 I began working as a senior developer for a small company building dynamic Web sites in the automotive industry. I spent five years at Dealerskins helping grow the company from 300 Web sites to 2,200 Web sites in 2008.\n\nI left Dealerskins in 2009 to help form an automotive startup focused on big data solutions. I served Dataium as Chief Technology Officer from December 2009 through December 2014. My role at Dataium involved managing the technology staff and leading the technology vision to build the entire technology stack from a blank sheet of paper. Some of our accomplishments include engineering an Apache Hadoop-based platform which processed hundreds of gigabytes each day into a multi-terabyte data warehouse. We also created a Web Services system using Linux, Node.js, and MySQL (later MongoDB) which processed over 3.3 billion HTTP transactions in March, 2015.\n\nDataium was sold to IHS in March 2015.\n\nIn May 2015 I started a new journey with the technology healthcare firm, Concert Genetics. My role as Vice President of Engineering involves hands-on programming and leading the amazing engineering team. We are reinventing how people think about and interact with the genetics testing marketplace.

summary: Data Architect / Database Architect / Database Administrator / DBA with 20+ years of progressive experience in IT and 15+ years of strong and deep experience in database design, data modeling, data integration, administration, data architecture with a sound knowledge of enterprise data architecture concepts with rapid prototyping and complete software development cycle. Real hands on experience for designing and building mission critical, high volume transaction and highly scalable data warehouse systems across globally distributed data centers with some of the very reputed fortune 500 organizations as well as fast paced start-up.\n\nCore competency areas:\nDatabase Analysis and Designing, Data modeling\nDatabase Administration and Database Management\nData Architecture \nData Governance \nData Security\nData Quality , Master Data Management ( MDM )\nData replications\nHigh Availability Exercise HA\nDisaster Recovery Drills DR\nOnline Transaction Processing ( OLTP )\nData Warehousing DW\nData Extraction Transformation Loading ETL , Extraction Loading Transformation ELT \nData Center migration \nOS Shell Scripting\nVery large database VLDB using table partitions and compression\nBusiness Intelligence BI \nOnline Analytical Processing OLAP\nEnterprise Architecture Framework - Zachman, TOGAF\n\nExpertise on technologies from all major RDBMS vendors:\nRDBMS: Oracle, MS-SQL Server,, Sybase, IBM-DB2 \nDatabase Replication: Oracle Golden Gate, Microsoft and Sybase \nDataWareHousing: Oracle DW, MS SQL Server, Sybase IQ \n\nCertified DBA : Oracle, Sybase and DB2\nCertified Replication DBA : Sybase\nCertified Hadoop Admin : Cloudera CDH4\n\nData Auditing Standards Familiarity: SAS-70, Sarbanes Oxley\n\nOpenSource and NoSQL Database familiarity\nNoSQL MongoDB (Certified completion for M102: MongoDB for DBAs) \nOpen Source MySQL\n\nHadoop / BIG Data / BigData\nCloudera Data Analyst Training: Using Pig, Hive, and Impala with Hadoop (Jan 2014)\nCloudera Administrator Training for Apache Hadoop (Jan 2014)

summary: ✔ Corp to Corp ~ 60% Remote ~ DC Metro \n✖ W2 ~ 100% Onsite ~ Relocation \n\nSUMMARY \n‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\nI’m a Full Stack Developer who has been doing software development & architecture work in Ruby/JavaScript/Java for a while now. \n\nIf you need development or architectural help and can engage on a Corp to Corp basis, reach out to me. While I prefer to do most of my work remotely, I have no issues with being onsite up to 2 days per week so long as the client is in the DC Metro Area.\n\nTECHNOLOGIES \n‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\nHere is a quick list of some of the technologies I've worked on in the recent past.\n\n✶ JavaScript: MeteorJS, ReactJS, Backbone.js, Node.js, Marionette.js\n✶ Ruby: Ruby on Rails, Sinatra, Grape, Rack\n✶ Java: Spring, Hibernate, Liferay, RichFaces, WebCenter\n✶ Databases: MongoDB, MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL, Redis\n✶ Deployment: EC2, AWS, Docker\n✶ Servers: Passenger, Tomcat, Nginx, JBoss  \n\nROLES \n‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\nHere are a few different ways I can help.\n\nAs an Architect ➡ You need help architecting a new product from scratch, or improving an existing one to make it more current, performant, scalable or maintainable.\n\nAs a Developer ➡ You need help leading a development team, or are looking for an independent contributor to help out with development.\n\nAs a Product Manager ➡ You need help defining the product requirements, or want someone to work closely & as a liaison between the product owners & developers.\n\nAs a Technical Project Manager ➡ You need help with product delivery.\n\nAs A Good Problem Solver ➡ You have a varying list of ever changing software engineering needs and need someone who can do a bit of everything!\n\nLINKS \n‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\n✶ Company Website: http://snowpal.software\n✶ Company Profile: http://tinyurl.com/j3e2y7t\n✶ Blog: http://snowpalsoftware.wordpress.com\n✶ My Profile as an Infographic: http://snowpal.software/krish\n\nWHEN LOOKING\n‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾\n✶ Corp to Corp ~ >= 60% Remote ~ DC Metro ~ No Relocation\n✶ Time & Materials (or) Fixed Price contracts.
